ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CombinedVersion
ChiNode.Notes: The combined version denotes the versions of the subpackages that have been combined into the total CIIMmodel. This is a convenience instead of having to look at each subpackage.

ChiValue.Name: date
ChiValue.Notes: Form is YYYY-MM-DD for example for January 5, 2009 it is 2009-01-05.

ChiValue.Name: version
ChiValue.Notes: Form is IEC61970CIMXXvYY_IEC61968CIMXXvYY_combined where XX is the major CIM package version and the YY is the minor version, and different packages could have different major and minor versions. For example IEC61970CIM13v18_IEC61968CIM10v16_combined. Additional packages might be added in the future.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ControlAreaOperator
ChiNode.Notes: Operates the Control Area. Approves and implements energy transactions. Verifies both Inter-Control Area and Intra-Control Area transactions for the power system before granting approval (and implementing) the transactions.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CustomerConsumer
ChiNode.Notes: The energy buyer in the energy marketplace.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GenerationProvider
ChiNode.Notes: The energy seller in the energy marketplace.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: IntSchedAgreement
ChiNode.Notes: A type of agreement that provides the default method by which interchange schedules are to be integrated to obtain hourly energy schedules for accounting.

ChiValue.Name: defaultIntegrationMethod
ChiValue.Notes: The default method by which interchange schedules are to be integrated to obtain hourly energy schedules for accounting. Method #1 is to integrate the instantaneous schedule between the hourly boundaries. Method #2 compensates for any up/down ramping that occurs across the hourly boundary (this is called block accounting).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Marketer
ChiNode.Notes: Matches buyers and sellers, and secures transmission (and other ancillary services) needed to complete the energy transaction.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: OpenAccessProduct
ChiNode.Notes: Contracts for services offered commercially.

ChiValue.Name: transmissionProductType
ChiValue.Notes: Type of the transmission product. This could be a transmission service class (firm, total transmission capability, or non-firm), transmission service period (on-peak, full-period, off-peak), transmission service increments (yearly extended, hourly fixed, monthly sliding, etc.), transmission service type (network, available transmission capability, or point-to-point, or a transmission service window (fixed hourly, sliding weekly, extended monthly, etc.).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TransmissionProvider
ChiNode.Notes: Provider of the transmission capacity (interconnecting wires between Generation and Consumption) required to fulfill and Energy Transaction's energy exchange. Posts information for transmission paths and AvailableTransmissionCapacities on a reservation node. Buys and sells its products and services on the same reservation node.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: IEC61968CIMVersion
ChiNode.Notes: IEC 61968 version number assigned to this UML model file.

ChiValue.Name: date
ChiValue.Notes: Form is YYYY-MM-DD for example for January 5, 2009 it is 2009-01-05.

ChiValue.Name: version
ChiValue.Notes: Form is IEC61968CIMXXvYY where XX is the major CIM package version and the YY is the minor version. For example IEC61968CIM10v17.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AreaReserveSpec
ChiNode.Notes: The control area's reserve specification

ChiValue.Name: areaReserveSpecName
ChiValue.Notes: The Identification or name of the control area's reserve specification. A particular specification could correspond to pre-defined power system conditions, e.g., emergency situations.

ChiValue.Name: lowerRegMarginReqt
ChiValue.Notes: Lower active power regulating margin requirement, the amount of generation that can be dropped by control in 10 minutes

ChiValue.Name: opReserveReqt
ChiValue.Notes: Operating active power reserve requirement, where operating reserve is the generating capability that is fully available within 30 minutes. Operating reserve is composed of primary reserve (t less than 10 min) and secondary reserve (10 less than t less than 30 min).

ChiValue.Name: primaryReserveReqt
ChiValue.Notes: Primary active power reserve requirement, where primary reserve is generating capability that is fully available within 10 minutes. Primary reserve is composed of spinning reserve and quick-start reserve.

ChiValue.Name: raiseRegMarginReqt
ChiValue.Notes: Raise active power regulating margin requirement, the amount of generation that can be picked up by control in 10 minutes

ChiValue.Name: spinningReserveReqt
ChiValue.Notes: Spinning active power reserve requirement, spinning reserve is generating capability that is presently synchronized to the network and is fully available within 10 minutes

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AvailableTransmissionCapacity
ChiNode.Notes: Amount of possible flow by direction.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Block
ChiNode.Notes: A block is a simple transaction type, with no additional relationships.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CurtailmentProfile
ChiNode.Notes: Curtailing entity must be providing at least one service to the EnergyTransaction. The CurtailmentProfile must be completely contained within the EnergyProfile timeframe for this EnergyTransaction.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Dynamic
ChiNode.Notes: A dynamic energy transaction has more complex relationships than a simple block type. It behaves like a pseudo tie line.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: DynamicSchedule
ChiNode.Notes: A continuously variable component of a control area's active power net interchange schedule. Dynamic schedules are sent and received by control areas.

ChiValue.Name: dynSchedSignRev
ChiValue.Notes: Dynamic schedule sign reversal required (yes/no)

ChiValue.Name: dynSchedStatus
ChiValue.Notes: The "active" or "inactive" status of the dynamic schedule

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: EnergyProduct
ChiNode.Notes: An EnergyProduct is offered commercially as a ContractOrTariff.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: EnergyProfile
ChiNode.Notes: Specifies the start time, stop time, level for an EnergyTransaction.

ChiValue.Name: version
ChiValue.Notes: v 4 moved SubControlArea

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: EnergyTransaction
ChiNode.Notes: Specifies the schedule for energy transfers between interchange areas that are necessary to satisfy the associated interchange transaction.

ChiValue.Name: firmInterchangeFlag
ChiValue.Notes: Firm interchange flag indicates whether or not this energy transaction can be changed without potential financial consequences.

ChiValue.Name: state
ChiValue.Notes: { Approve | Deny | Study }

ChiValue.Name: energyMin
ChiValue.Notes: Transaction minimum active power if dispatchable

ChiValue.Name: congestChargeMax
ChiValue.Notes: Maximum congestion charges in monetary units

ChiValue.Name: receiptPointP
ChiValue.Notes: Receipt point active power

ChiValue.Name: deliveryPointP
ChiValue.Notes: Delivery point active power

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: HostControlArea
ChiNode.Notes: A HostControlArea has a set of tie points and a set of generator controls (i.e., AGC). It also has a total load, including transmission and distribution losses.

ChiValue.Name: areaControlMode
ChiValue.Notes: The area's present control mode: (CF = constant frequency) or (CTL = constant tie-line) or (TLB = tie-line bias) or (OFF = off control)

ChiValue.Name: freqSetPoint
ChiValue.Notes: The present power system frequency set point for automatic generation control

ChiValue.Name: frequencyBiasFactor
ChiValue.Notes: The control area's frequency bias factor, in active power per frequency, for automatic generation control (AGC)

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: InadvertentAccount
ChiNode.Notes: An account for tracking inadvertent interchange versus time for each control area. A control area may have more than one inadvertent account in order to track inadvertent over one or more specific tie points in addition to the usual overall net inadvertent. Separate accounts would also be used to track designated time periods, such as on-peak and off-peak.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: LossProfile
ChiNode.Notes: LossProfile is associated with an EnerrgyTransaction and must be completely contained within the time frame of the EnergyProfile associated with this EnergyTransaction.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Profile
ChiNode.Notes: A profile is a simpler curve type.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ProfileData
ChiNode.Notes: Data for profile.

ChiValue.Name: sequenceNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Sequence to provide item numbering for the profile. { greater than or equal to 1 }

ChiValue.Name: startDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Start date/time for this profile.

ChiValue.Name: stopDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Stop date/time for this profile.

ChiValue.Name: capacityLevel
ChiValue.Notes: Active power capacity level for the profile.

ChiValue.Name: energyLevel
ChiValue.Notes: Energy level for the profile

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: SubControlArea
ChiNode.Notes:
SubControlArea replacement classed moved into EnergySchedulingPackage.
An area defined for the purpose of tracking interchange with surrounding areas via tie points; may or may not serve as a control area.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TransmissionCorridor
ChiNode.Notes: A corridor containing one or more rights of way

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TransmissionRightOfWay
ChiNode.Notes: A collection of transmission lines that are close proximity to each other.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AssetModel
ChiNode.Notes:
Documentation for a type of an asset of a particular product model made by a manufacturer (Organisation). There are typically many instances of an asset associated with a single asset model.
Note that the type of AssetModel is determined by the TypeAsset associated with it.

ChiValue.Name: modelNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Manufacturer's model number.

ChiValue.Name: modelVersion
ChiValue.Notes: Version number for product model, which indicates vintage of the product.

ChiValue.Name: corporateStandardKind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of coporate standard for this asset model.

ChiValue.Name: usageKind
ChiValue.Notes: Intended usage for this asset model.

ChiValue.Name: weightTotal
ChiValue.Notes: Total manufactured weight of asset.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ElectricalAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of ElectricalAsset of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: EndDeviceModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of End Device of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: MeterAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of a meter asset of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiValue.Name: wireCount
ChiValue.Notes: Number of wires.

ChiValue.Name: form
ChiValue.Notes: Meter form number.

ChiValue.Name: kH
ChiValue.Notes: Meter kh (watthour) constant. This constant is the number of watthours that must be applied to the meter to cause one disk revolution for an electromechanical meter or the number of watthours represented by one increment pulse for an electronic meter.

ChiValue.Name: maxRegisterCount
ChiValue.Notes: Maximum number of registers this meter model can support. The actual number in use is based on the number of Registers associated with a given MeterAsset.

ChiValue.Name: registerRatio
ChiValue.Notes: Meter register ratio.

ChiValue.Name: timeOfUseMeter
ChiValue.Notes: True when the meter or meter+AMR module are capable of offering TOU data.

ChiValue.Name: kwhMeter
ChiValue.Notes: True when the meter is capable of metering real energy in kWh.

ChiValue.Name: kVAhMeter
ChiValue.Notes: True when the meter is capable of metering apparent energy in kVAh.

ChiValue.Name: demandMeter
ChiValue.Notes: True when the meter or installed AMR option is capable of capturing demand data.

ChiValue.Name: reactiveMeter
ChiValue.Notes: True when the meter is capable of metering reactive energy in kVArh.

ChiValue.Name: qMeter
ChiValue.Notes: True when the meter is capable of metering reactive energy in kQh.

ChiValue.Name: loadProfileMeter
ChiValue.Notes: True when the meter or the installed AMR option is capable of capturing kWh interval data.

ChiValue.Name: intervalDataMeter
ChiValue.Notes: True when the meter or the installed AMR option is capable of capturing interval data for a user selectable measurement (kWh, Volts, or some other billing or engineering quantity).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Asset
ChiNode.Notes: Tangible resource of the utility, including power system equipment, cabinets, buildings, etc. For electrical network equipment, the role of the asset is defined in the Wires Model (refer to IEC 61970-301). This role is associated with an asset description, which places emphasis on the physical characteristics of the equipment fulfilling that role.

ChiValue.Name: corporateCode
ChiValue.Notes: Code for this type of asset.

ChiValue.Name: category
ChiValue.Notes: Extension mechanism to accommodate utility-specific categorisation of Asset and its subtypes, according to their corporate standards, practices, and existing IT systems (e.g., for management of assets, maintenance, work, outage, customers, etc.).

ChiValue.Name: utcNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Uniquely Tracked Commodity (UTC) number.

ChiValue.Name: serialNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Serial number of asset.

ChiValue.Name: lotNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Lot number for this asset. Even for the same model and version number, many assets are manufactured in lots.

ChiValue.Name: manufacturedDate
ChiValue.Notes: Date asset was manufactured.

ChiValue.Name: purchasePrice
ChiValue.Notes: Purchase price of asset.

ChiValue.Name: critical
ChiValue.Notes: True if asset is considered critical for some reason (for example, a pole with critical attachments).

ChiValue.Name: application
ChiValue.Notes: The way this particular asset is being used in this installation. For example, the application of a bushing when attached to a specific transformer winding would be one of the following: H1, H2, H3, H0, X1, X2, X3, X0, Y1, Y2, Y3, Y0.

ChiValue.Name: installationDate
ChiValue.Notes: Date current installation was completed, which may not be the same as the in-service date. Asset may have been installed at other locations previously. Ignored if asset is (1) not currently installed (e.g., stored in a depot) or (2) not intended to be installed (e.g., vehicle, tool).

ChiValue.Name: initialCondition
ChiValue.Notes: Condition of asset in inventory or at time of installation. Examples include new, rebuilt, overhaul required, other. Refer to inspection data for information on the most current condition of the asset.

ChiValue.Name: testStatus
ChiValue.Notes: True if asset has passed acceptance test and may be placed in or is in service. The type of tests or group of tests is identified in'testType'. It is returned to a false state if asset is removed from service and is required to be tested again before being placed back in service, possibly in a new location. The date of each acceptance test (device may go through multiple test during its life cycle) is determined in AssetStatus.

ChiValue.Name: testDate
ChiValue.Notes: The date and time this asset was last tested using the 'testType' and yiedling the currnet status in 'testStatus'.

ChiValue.Name: testType
ChiValue.Notes: The type of test or group of tests that was conducted on 'testDate'.

ChiValue.Name: initialLossOfLife
ChiValue.Notes: Zero for new devices. Whenever an asset is reconditioned, this is the percentage of expected life for the asset when it was new.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AssetContainer
ChiNode.Notes: Asset that is aggregation of other assets such as conductors, transformers, switchgear, land, fences, buildings, equipment, vehicles, etc.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AssetFunction
ChiNode.Notes: Function performed by an asset. Often, function is a module (or a board that plugs into a backplane) that can be replaced or updated without impacting the rest of the asset. Therefore functions are treated as assets because they have life-cycles that are independent of the asset containing the function.

ChiValue.Name: firmwareID
ChiValue.Notes: Firmware version.

ChiValue.Name: hardwareID
ChiValue.Notes: Hardware version.

ChiValue.Name: password
ChiValue.Notes: Password needed to access asset function.

ChiValue.Name: configID
ChiValue.Notes: Configuration specified for this function.

ChiValue.Name: programID
ChiValue.Notes: Name of program.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ElectricalInfo
ChiNode.Notes:
Used to define either the required electrical properties of a type of asset, the actual electrical properties of an asset model or the actual electrical properties of a particular asset. An ElectricalTypeAsset or ElectricalAssetModel may have multiple ElectricalProperties associated with it, with the ElecTAElecPropRole/ElecAMElecPropRole defining which roles in the Asset these properties refer to. e.g. a Transformer TypeAsset or AssetModel will have an ElectricalProperties association for each winding.
This can also be used to define ElectricalProperties for each phase individually by using the phases attribute thus allowing an ElectricalTypeAsset or ElectricalAssetModel to have an individual entry for each phase.
Not every property will be required for each type of ElectricalTypeAsset. E.g. a Transformer may only have requirments for 'ratedVoltage', 'ratedApparentPower' and phases, while a LinearConductor will have r,x,b and g requirements per unitLength on top of a 'ratedCurrent' and 'ratedVoltage'.

ChiValue.Name: r
ChiValue.Notes: Positive sequence series resistance.

ChiValue.Name: x
ChiValue.Notes: Positive sequence series reactance

ChiValue.Name: b
ChiValue.Notes: Positive sequence susceptance

ChiValue.Name: g
ChiValue.Notes: Positive sequence conductance

ChiValue.Name: r0
ChiValue.Notes: Zero sequence series resistance

ChiValue.Name: x0
ChiValue.Notes: Zero sequence series reactance

ChiValue.Name: b0
ChiValue.Notes: Zero sequence susceptance

ChiValue.Name: g0
ChiValue.Notes: Zero sequence conductance

ChiValue.Name: ratedVoltage
ChiValue.Notes: Rated voltage.

ChiValue.Name: ratedApparentPower
ChiValue.Notes: Rated apparent power.

ChiValue.Name: ratedCurrent
ChiValue.Notes: Rated current.

ChiValue.Name: bil
ChiValue.Notes:
Basic Insulation Level (BIL) for switchgear, insulators, etc.
A reference insulation level expressed as the impulse crest voltage of a nominal wave, typically 1.2 X 50 microsecond. This is a measure of the ability of the insulation to withstand very high voltage surges.

ChiValue.Name: frequency
ChiValue.Notes: Frequency at which stated device ratings apply, typically 50 Hz or 60 Hz.

ChiValue.Name: phaseCount
ChiValue.Notes: Number of potential phases this type of asset supports, typically 0, 1 or 3. The actual phases connected are determined from the 'phases' attribute in the associtead Wires hierarchy class (inherited from ConductingEquipment). The number of phases connected may be dervied from 'phaseCode' attribute.

ChiValue.Name: wireCount
ChiValue.Notes: For an installed asset, this is the total number of electrical wires that are physically connected to it. For a TypeAsset or AssetModel, this is the total number of wires that can potentially be connected to this asset type. This is particularly useful to understand overall electrical configurations for distribution secondary where the number of wires can not be derived from phase information alone. For example, 120v 2 Wires; 240v 2 Wires; 480v 1Ph 2 Wires; 120/240v 1Ph; 120/208v 3Ph Y; 120/208v 1Ph Y; 120/240v 3Ph D; 240/480v 1Ph 3 Wires; 480v 3Ph D; 240/480v 3Ph D; 277/480v 3Ph Y.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Seal
ChiNode.Notes: Physically controls access to AssetContainers.

ChiValue.Name: sealNumber
ChiValue.Notes: (reserved word) Seal number.

ChiValue.Name: kind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of seal.

ChiValue.Name: condition
ChiValue.Notes: Condition of seal.

ChiValue.Name: appliedDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time the seal has been applied.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ComEquipmentAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Communicaiton equipment, other than media, such as gateways, routers, controllers, etc.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ActivityRecord
ChiNode.Notes: Records activity for an Asset, Location, Document, PowerSystemResource, Organisation or ErpContact (e.g., operator, market participant, etc.) at a point in time. An activity may be for an event that has already occurred or for a planned activity. The PowerSystemResource relationship records events regarding the logical function being provided by the resource in the electrical network (independent of the particular asset providing the function). The Asset relationship records history about the particular equipment, independent of where it is currently being used in the electrical network. The Location relationship records events associated with the geographical location. The Customer relationship records history regarding the customer independent of the logical network or particular assets being used to serve the customer.

ChiValue.Name: createdDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time this Activity Record has been created (different from the 'status.dateTime', which is the time of a status change of the associated object, if applicable).

ChiValue.Name: category
ChiValue.Notes: Category of event resulting in this ActivityRecord.

ChiValue.Name: severity
ChiValue.Notes: Severity level of event resulting in this ActivityRecord.

ChiValue.Name: reason
ChiValue.Notes: Description of reason for event resulting in this ActivityRecord, typically supplied when user initiated.

ChiValue.Name: status
ChiValue.Notes: Inofrmation on consequence of event resulting in this ActivityRecord.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Agreement
ChiNode.Notes: Formal agreement between two parties defining the terms and conditions for a set of services. The specifics of the services are, in turn, defined via one or more service agreements.

ChiValue.Name: signDate
ChiValue.Notes: Date this agreement was consumated among associated persons and/or organisations.

ChiValue.Name: validityInterval
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time interval this agreement is valid (from going into effect to termination).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: DateTimeInterval
ChiNode.Notes: Interval of date and time.

ChiValue.Name: start
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time that this interval started.

ChiValue.Name: end
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time that this interval ended.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Document
ChiNode.Notes: Parent class for different groupings of information that is collected and managed as a part of a business process. It will frequently contain references to other objects, such as assets, people and power system resources.

ChiValue.Name: createdDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time that this document was created.

ChiValue.Name: lastModifiedDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time the document was last modified. Documents may potentially be modified many times during their lifetime.

ChiValue.Name: revisionNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Revision number for the document.

ChiValue.Name: subject
ChiValue.Notes: Main subject for this document.

ChiValue.Name: title
ChiValue.Notes: Title of the document.

ChiValue.Name: docStatus
ChiValue.Notes:
Status of the document; for status of subject metter this document represents, use 'status'.
Example values for 'docStatus.status' are draft, approved, cancelled, etc.

ChiValue.Name: category
ChiValue.Notes: Extension mechanism to accommodate utility-specific categorisation of Document and its subtypes, according to their corporate standards, practices, and existing IT systems (e.g., for management of assets, maintenance, work, outage, customers, etc.).

ChiValue.Name: status
ChiValue.Notes: Status of subject metter this document represents; for status of the document itself, use 'docStatus'.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ElectronicAddress
ChiNode.Notes: Electronic address information.

ChiValue.Name: email
ChiValue.Notes: Email address.

ChiValue.Name: lan
ChiValue.Notes: Address on local area network.

ChiValue.Name: web
ChiValue.Notes: World Wide Web address.

ChiValue.Name: radio
ChiValue.Notes: Radio address.

ChiValue.Name: userID
ChiValue.Notes: The user ID needed to log in, which can be for an individual person (associated with ErpPerson), an Organisation, a Location, etc.

ChiValue.Name: password
ChiValue.Notes: Password needed to log in.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Location
ChiNode.Notes: The place, scene, or point of something where someone or something has been, is, and/or will be at a given moment in time. It may be the spatial location of an actual or planned structure or set of point-oriented structures (as a substation, structure, building, town, etc.), which may be defined as a point or polygon. It may also be the path of an underground or overhead conductor.

ChiValue.Name: corporateCode
ChiValue.Notes: Utility-specific code for the location.

ChiValue.Name: category
ChiValue.Notes: Category by utility's corporate standards and practices, relative to the location itself (e.g., geographical, functional accounting, etc.), not a given Property that happens to exist at that location.

ChiValue.Name: mainAddress
ChiValue.Notes: Street address of the location.

ChiValue.Name: secondaryAddress
ChiValue.Notes: Secondary address of the location. For example, PO Box address may have different ZIP code than that in the 'mainAddress' and then you can use this attribute.

ChiValue.Name: direction
ChiValue.Notes: Direction that allows field crews to quickly find a given asset. For a given location, such as a street address, this is the relative direction in wich to find the asset. For example, a Streetlight may be located at the 'NW' (northwest) corner of the customer's site, or a ServiceDeliveryPoint may be located on the second floor of an appartment building.

ChiValue.Name: isPolygon
ChiValue.Notes: True if the first and last point in the sequence of coordinate pairs are to be connected, thus forming a polygon rather than merely a sequence of line segments.

ChiValue.Name: geoInfoReference
ChiValue.Notes: Reference to geographical information source, often external to the utility. The possessor of the source is identifed through associated Organisation.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Organisation
ChiNode.Notes: Identifies organisations that might have roles as utilities, contractors, suppliers, manufacturers, customers, etc. Identifies organisations that might have roles as utilities, contractors, suppliers, manufacturers, customers, etc.

ChiValue.Name: streetAddress
ChiValue.Notes: Street address.

ChiValue.Name: postalAddress
ChiValue.Notes: Postal address, potentially different than 'streetAddress' (e.g., another city).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Status
ChiNode.Notes:
Current status information relevant to many types of objects.
Note that this status is always regarding the object's subject matter. For example, the status of a given WorkTask, not the status of the documentation for a WorkTask.
Design rationale: Because many utilities and product vendors prefer not to delete objects, but rather keep them for eternity, but marked as cancelled, invalid, terminated, etc., it is necessary to have, as a minimum, status (on whether the object is pending, active, cancelled, etc.) and the date that it went into that state.

ChiValue.Name: dateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time for which 'status' applies.

ChiValue.Name: remark
ChiValue.Notes: Pertinent information regarding the current 'status'. This is generally free form text.

ChiValue.Name: reason
ChiValue.Notes: Reason code or explanation for why this object went to the current status.

ChiValue.Name: value
ChiValue.Notes:
The value of this status at the time of 'dateTime'. Refer to instances of associated ActivityRecords for prior states.
Note that for types of documents, the status is regarding the subject matter (e.g., TroubleTicket, SwitchingSchedule, Work, WorkTask, Specification, TypeAsset, AssetModel, etc.) of this particular type of document. It is not the status of the document, which is found in 'docStatus'.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: StreetAddress
ChiNode.Notes: General purpose address information.

ChiValue.Name: streetName
ChiValue.Notes: The name of the street.

ChiValue.Name: streetNumber
ChiValue.Notes: The designator of the specific location on the street.

ChiValue.Name: streetSuffix
ChiValue.Notes: Suffix to the street name. For examle, North, South, East, West.

ChiValue.Name: streetPrefix
ChiValue.Notes: Prefix to the street name. For examle, North, South, East, West.

ChiValue.Name: streetType
ChiValue.Notes: Type of street. Examples include: street, circle, boulevard, avenue, road, drive, etc.

ChiValue.Name: poBox
ChiValue.Notes: The post office box.

ChiValue.Name: suiteNumber
ChiValue.Notes: The number of the apartment or suite.

ChiValue.Name: addressGeneral
ChiValue.Notes: Additional address information, for example a mailstop.

ChiValue.Name: townCode
ChiValue.Notes: The code for a particular town.

ChiValue.Name: section
ChiValue.Notes: A Section is part of a township. For example, it is common for there to be 36 section per township.

ChiValue.Name: city
ChiValue.Notes: Name of city.

ChiValue.Name: stateOrProvince
ChiValue.Notes: Name of the state or province.

ChiValue.Name: country
ChiValue.Notes: Name of the country.

ChiValue.Name: postalCode
ChiValue.Notes: Postal code for the address.

ChiValue.Name: withinCityLimits
ChiValue.Notes: True if this location is within the legal geographical boundaries of the specified city (default).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TelephoneNumber
ChiNode.Notes: Telephone number.

ChiValue.Name: areaCode
ChiValue.Notes: Area or region code.

ChiValue.Name: cityCode
ChiValue.Notes: (if applicable) City code.

ChiValue.Name: countryCode
ChiValue.Notes: Country code.

ChiValue.Name: localNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Main (local) part of this telephone number.

ChiValue.Name: extension
ChiValue.Notes: (if applicable) Extension for this telephone number.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TimeSchedule
ChiNode.Notes: Used for anything that needs to be described in terms of how it changes through time. An object of this class is used to perform a single-valued function of time. You may want to use 'category' to give additional info on this schedule, such as: periodic (hourly, daily, weekly, monthly, etc.), day of the month, by date, calendar (specific times and dates).

ChiValue.Name: disabled
ChiValue.Notes: True if the schedule is deactivated (disabled).

ChiValue.Name: startDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Schedule start date and time.

ChiValue.Name: endDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Scheduled end date and time.

ChiValue.Name: recurrencePattern
ChiValue.Notes: Interval at which an appointment repeats (e.g., first Monday of every month, last day of the month, etc.).

ChiValue.Name: recurrencePeriod
ChiValue.Notes: Duration between time points, from the beginning of one period to the beginning of the next period. Note that a device like a meter may have multiple interval periods (e.g., 1, 5, 15, 30, or 60 minutes).

ChiValue.Name: offset
ChiValue.Notes: The offset from midnight (i.e., 0 hours, 0 minutes, 0 seconds) for the periodic time points to begin. For example, for an interval meter that is set up for five minute intervals ('recurrencePeriod'=300=5 min), setting 'offset'=120=2 min would result in scheduled events to read the meter executing at 2, 7, 12, 17, 22, 27, 32, 37, 42, 47, 52, and 57 minutes past each hour.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: UserAttribute
ChiNode.Notes: Generic name-value pair class, with optional sequence number and units for value. Can be used to model parts of information exchange when concrete types are not known in advance.

ChiValue.Name: name
ChiValue.Notes: The name of an attribute.

ChiValue.Name: sequenceNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Sequence number for this attribute in a list of attributes, starting with 1.

ChiValue.Name: value
ChiValue.Notes: The value of an attribute, including unit information.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Customer
ChiNode.Notes: Organisation receiving services from ServiceSupplier.

ChiValue.Name: specialNeed
ChiValue.Notes: True if overall customer (vs. ErpPerson) have special service needs such as life support, hospitals, etc.

ChiValue.Name: kind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of customer.

ChiValue.Name: vip
ChiValue.Notes: True if this is an important customer. Importance is for matters different than special needs (reflected in 'specialNeeds' attribute).

ChiValue.Name: pucNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Public Utility Commission identification number, if applicable.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CustomerAccount
ChiNode.Notes: Assignment of a group of products and services purchased by the Customer through a CustomerAgreement, used as a mechanism for customer billing and payment. It collects together the CustomerAgreements to create billings (invoices) for a Customer and receive payment.

ChiValue.Name: billingCycle
ChiValue.Notes: Cycle day on which the related CustomerAccount will normally be billed. It is used to determine when to produce the CustomerBillingInfo for this CustomerAccount.

ChiValue.Name: budgetBill
ChiValue.Notes: Budget bill code.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CustomerAgreement
ChiNode.Notes: Agreement between the Customer and the ServiceSupplier to pay for service at a specific ServiceLocation. It records certain billing information about the type of service provided at the ServiceLocation and is used during charge creation to determine the type of service. CustomerAccount contains common information from the various types of CustomerAgreements.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: PricingStructure
ChiNode.Notes: Grouping of pricing components and prices used in the creation of customer charges and the eligibility criteria under which these terms may be offered to a customer. The reasons for grouping includes state, customer classification, site characteristics, classification (i.e. fee price structure, deposit price structure, electric service price structure, etc.) and accounting requirements.

ChiValue.Name: code
ChiValue.Notes: Unique user-allocated key for a PricingStructure, used by company representatives to identify the correct price structure for allocating to a customer. For rate schedules it is often prefixed by a state code.

ChiValue.Name: revenueKind
ChiValue.Notes: (Accounting) Kind of revenue, often used to determine the grace period allowed, before collection actions are taken on a customer (grace periods vary between revenue classes).

ChiValue.Name: taxExemption
ChiValue.Notes: True if the PricingStructure is taxable.

ChiValue.Name: dailyEstimatedUsage
ChiValue.Notes: Used in place of actual computed estimated average when history of usage is not available, and typically manually entered by customer accounting.

ChiValue.Name: dailyCeilingUsage
ChiValue.Notes: Absolute maximum valid non-demand usage quantity used in validating a customer's billed non-demand usage.

ChiValue.Name: dailyFloorUsage
ChiValue.Notes: Absolute minimum valid non-demand usage quantity used in validating a customer's billed non-demand usage.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ServiceCategory
ChiNode.Notes: Category of service provided to the customer.

ChiValue.Name: kind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of service.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ServiceLocation
ChiNode.Notes:
A customer ServiceLocation has one or more ServiceDeliveryPoint(s), which in turn relate to Meters. The location may be a point or a polygon, depending on the specific circumstances.
For distribution, the ServiceLocation is typically the location of the utility customer's premise. Because a customer's premise may have one or more meters, the ServiceDeliveryPoint is used to define the actual conducting equipment that the EndDeviceAsset attaches to at the utility customer's ServiceLocation.
For transmission, it is the point(s) of interconnection on the transmission provider's transmission system where capacity and/or energy transmitted by the transmission provider is made available to the receiving party.

ChiValue.Name: accessMethod
ChiValue.Notes: Method for the service person to access the appropriate service locations. For example, a description of where to obtain a key if the facility is unmanned and secured.

ChiValue.Name: siteAccessProblem
ChiValue.Notes: Problems previously encountered when visiting or performing work on this site. Examples include: bad dog, viloent customer, verbally abusive occupant, obstructions, safety hazards, etc.

ChiValue.Name: needsInspection
ChiValue.Notes: True if inspection is needed of facilities at this service location. This could be requested by a customer, due to suspected tampering, environmental concerns (e.g., a fire in the vicinity), or to correct incompatible data.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Tariff
ChiNode.Notes: Document, approved by the responsible regulatory agency, listing the terms and conditions, including a schedule of prices, under which utility services will be provided. It has a unique number within the state or province. For Rate Schedules it is frequently allocated by the affiliated Public Utilities Commission.

ChiValue.Name: endDate
ChiValue.Notes: (if tariff became inactive) Date tarrif was terminated.

ChiValue.Name: startDate
ChiValue.Notes: Date tarrif was activated.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AssetFunctionAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of an asset function of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.(Organisation). Asset Functions are typically component parts of Assets or Asset Containers.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AssetModelCatalogue
ChiNode.Notes: Catalogue of available types of products and materials that are used to build or install, maintain or operate an Asset. Each catalogue item is for a specific product (AssetModel) available from a specific supplier.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AssetModelCatalogueItem
ChiNode.Notes: Provides pricing and other relevant information about a specific manufacturer's product (i.e., AssetModel), and its price from a given supplier. A single AssetModel may be availble from multiple suppliers. Note that manufacturer and supplier are both types of organisation, which the association is inherited from Document.

ChiValue.Name: unitCost
ChiValue.Notes: Unit cost for an asset model from a specific supplier, either for a unit cost or cost per unit length. Cost is for material or asset only and does not include labor to install/construct or configure it.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: BreakerAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of a breaker asset of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: BusbarAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of a busbar asset of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: BushingModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of a bushing of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiValue.Name: insulationKind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of insulation used in this bushing model.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CabinetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of Cabinet of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CableAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of a Cable of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiValue.Name: insulationThickness
ChiValue.Notes: Thickness of the insulation.

ChiValue.Name: insulatingCompound
ChiValue.Notes: Insulating compound name.

ChiValue.Name: outerJacketKind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of outer jacket of this cable.

ChiValue.Name: neutralCondDesign
ChiValue.Notes: Neutral conductor design: Concentric Neutral, Copper Tape, Aluminum Tape, Lead insulation, Other.

ChiValue.Name: strandFillFlag
ChiValue.Notes: True if wire strands are extruded in a way to fill the voids in the cable.

ChiValue.Name: nominalTemp
ChiValue.Notes: Maximum nominal design operating temperature.

ChiValue.Name: conductorMaterialKind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of conductor material of this cable product.

ChiValue.Name: sheathMaterial
ChiValue.Notes: Sheath material: Lead, Copper, Steel, Aluminum, None.

ChiValue.Name: sheathNeutral
ChiValue.Notes: True if sheath is used as a neutral.

ChiValue.Name: constructionKind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of construction of this cable product.

ChiValue.Name: shieldKind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of conductor shield of this cable product.

ChiValue.Name: conductorCount
ChiValue.Notes: Number of conductors physically contained in the cable.

ChiValue.Name: centerToNeutral
ChiValue.Notes: Center to neutral conductor spacing for a concentric neutral cable (blank for a transmission model).

ChiValue.Name: diameterToNeutral
ChiValue.Notes: Diameter of a concentric neutral strand for a concentric neutral cable.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ComFunctionAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of communication function of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CompositeSwitchAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of a composite switch asset of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CurrentTransformerAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: A particular model supplied by a manufacturer of a Current Transformer (CT), wich is used to measure electrical qualities of the circuit that is being protected and/or monitored.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: FACTSDeviceAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes:
A particular model of FACTS device provided from a manufacturer. A FACTS devices are used for the dynamic control of voltage, impedance and phase angle of high voltage AC transmission lines.
FACTS device types include:
- SVC = Static Var Compensator
- STATCOM = Static Synchronous Compensator
- TCPAR = Thyristor Controlled Phase-Angle Regulator
- TCSC = Thyristor Controlled Series Capacitor
- TCVL = Thyristor Controlled Voltage Limiter
- TSBR = Thyristor Switched Braking Resistor
- TSSC = Thyristor Switched Series Capacitor
- UPFC = Unified Power Flow Controller

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: FaultIndicatorAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of an FaultIndicator asset of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GeneratorAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of generation equipment of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: LinearConductorAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: A type of linear conductor made by a particular manufacturer (Organisation). Its ElectricalProperties are defined as being per unit length (which is defined by the unitLength attribute)

ChiValue.Name: insulated
ChiValue.Notes: True if conductor is insultated.

ChiValue.Name: insulationKind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of insulation material.

ChiValue.Name: usage
ChiValue.Notes: Usage of this linear conductor product.

ChiValue.Name: radius
ChiValue.Notes: Radius of the conductor

ChiValue.Name: size
ChiValue.Notes: Commonly referred to size for this type of conductor.

ChiValue.Name: gMR
ChiValue.Notes: Geometric Mean Radius. If the conductor were replaced by a thin walled tube of radius gMR then its reactance would be identical to that of the actual conductor

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: OverheadConductorAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: A type of linear conductor model made by a particular manufacturer (Organisation). Its ElectricalProperties are defined as being per unit length (which is defined by the unitLength attribute)

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: PoleModel
ChiNode.Notes: A type of pole supplied by a given manufacturer.

ChiValue.Name: classification
ChiValue.Notes: Pole class: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, H1, H2, Other, Unknown.

ChiValue.Name: speciesType
ChiValue.Notes: Pole species. Aluminum, Aluminum Davit, Concrete, Fiberglass, Galvanized Davit, Galvanized, Steel Davit Primed, Steel Davit, Steel Standard Primed, Steel, Truncated, Wood-Treated, Wood-Hard, Wood-Salt Treated, Wood-Soft, Wood, Other, Unknown.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: PotentialTransformerAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: A particular model supplied by a manufacturer of a Potential Transformer (PT), wich is used to measure electrical qualities of the circuit that is being protected and/or monitored.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ProtectionEquipmentAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of protection equipment asset of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: RecloserAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of a recloser asset of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ResistorAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of a resistor asset of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: SeriesCompensatorAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: For application as a series capacitor or reactor, this is documentation for a type of a capacitor or reactor of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ShuntCompensatorAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: For application as shunt capacitor or reactor or switchable bank of shunt capacitors or reactors, this is documentation for a type of a capacitor or reactor of a particular product model made by a manufacturer (Organisation). There are typically many instances of an asset associated with a single asset model.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: StreetlightAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of a streelight of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiValue.Name: lampKind
ChiValue.Notes: Lamp kind supplied from manufacturer (vs. one that has been replaced in the field).

ChiValue.Name: lightRating
ChiValue.Notes: Power rating of light as supplied by the manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: SurgeProtectorAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of an SurgeProtector asset of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: SVCAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of a Static Var Compensator of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: SwitchAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of a switch asset of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TapChangerModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of a tap changer of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiValue.Name: switchingKind
ChiValue.Notes: Switching kind of tap changer.

ChiValue.Name: tapCount
ChiValue.Notes: Number of taps.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ToolAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of a tool of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TowerAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: A type of tower supplied by a given manufacturer or constructed from a common design.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TransformerAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of a transformer of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiValue.Name: autoTransformer
ChiValue.Notes: True if this is an autotransformer, false otherwise.

ChiValue.Name: coreKind
ChiValue.Notes: Core kind of this transformer product.

ChiValue.Name: windingInsulationKind
ChiValue.Notes:
Type of insultation used for transformer windings:
Paper, Thermally Upgraded Paper, Nomex, other

ChiValue.Name: oilPreservationKind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of oil preservation system.

ChiValue.Name: solidInsulationWeight
ChiValue.Notes: Weight of solid insultation in transformer.

ChiValue.Name: coreCoilsWeight
ChiValue.Notes: Weight of core and coils in transformer.

ChiValue.Name: neutralBIL
ChiValue.Notes: Basic Insulation Level of Neutral

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: VehicleAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of a vehicle of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: WorkEquipmentAssetModel
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of an equipment used for work of a particular product model made by a manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AssetAssetRole
ChiNode.Notes: Roles played between Assets and other Assets.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AssetPropertyCurve
ChiNode.Notes: An Asset Property that is described through curves rather than as a data point. The relationship is to be defined between an independent variable (X-axis) and one or two dependent variables (Y1-axis and Y2-axis).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AssetPsrRole
ChiNode.Notes: Roles played between Assets and Power System Resources.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: BushingInsulationPF
ChiNode.Notes:
Bushing insulation power factor condition as a result of a test.
Typical status values are: Acceptable, Minor Deterioration or Moisture Absorption, Major Deterioration or Moisture Absorption, Failed.

ChiValue.Name: testKind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of test for this bushing.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Cabinet
ChiNode.Notes: Enclosure that offers protection to the equipment it contains and/or safety to people/animals outside it.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: DimensionsInfo
ChiNode.Notes: As applicable, the basic linear, area, or volume dimensions of an asset, asset type (AssetModel) or other type of object (such as land area). Units and multipliers are specified per dimension.

ChiValue.Name: sizeDepth
ChiValue.Notes: Depth measurement.

ChiValue.Name: sizeLength
ChiValue.Notes: Length measurement.

ChiValue.Name: sizeWidth
ChiValue.Notes: Width measurement.

ChiValue.Name: sizeDiameter
ChiValue.Notes: Diameter measurement.

ChiValue.Name: orientation
ChiValue.Notes: A description of the orientation of the object relative to the dimensions. As an example, a vault may have north-south orientation for the sizeLength measurement and sizeDepth may be the height of the vault.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: DocAssetRole
ChiNode.Notes: Roles played between Documents and Assets.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ElectricalAsset
ChiNode.Notes: An asset that has (or can have) a role in the electrical network.

ChiValue.Name: isConnected
ChiValue.Notes: True if the asset is physically connected to electrical network (as opposed to being in a warehouse, being refurbished, etc.). Note that this attribute is not intended to imply energization status and/or whether the asset is actually being used.

ChiValue.Name: phaseCode
ChiValue.Notes: If 'isConnected' is true, then this is the as-built phase(s) that the asset is associatied with.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Facility
ChiNode.Notes: A facility may contain buildings, storage facilities, switching facilities, power generation, manufacturing facilities, maintenance facilities, etc.

ChiValue.Name: kind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of this facility.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: FailureEvent
ChiNode.Notes: An event where an asset has failed to perform its functions within specified parameters.

ChiValue.Name: corporateCode
ChiValue.Notes: Code for asset failure.

ChiValue.Name: failureIsolationMethod
ChiValue.Notes: How the asset failure was isolated from the system.

ChiValue.Name: faultLocatingMethod
ChiValue.Notes: The method used for locating the faulted part of the asset. For example, cable options include: Cap Discharge-Thumping, Bridge Method, Visual Inspection, Other.

ChiValue.Name: location
ChiValue.Notes: Failure location on an object.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: FinancialInfo
ChiNode.Notes: Various current financial properties associated with a particular asset. Historical properties may be determined by ActivityRecords associated with the asset.

ChiValue.Name: financialValue
ChiValue.Notes: Value of asset as of 'valueDate'.

ChiValue.Name: valueDate
ChiValue.Notes: The date and time at which the financial value was last established.

ChiValue.Name: plantTransferDate
ChiValue.Notes: Date asset's financial value was put in plant for regulatory accounting purposes (e.g., for rate base calculations). This is sometime referred to as the "in-service date."

ChiValue.Name: warrantyDate
ChiValue.Notes: Date warranty on asset expires.

ChiValue.Name: purchaseDate
ChiValue.Notes: Date asset was purchased.

ChiValue.Name: purchaseOrderNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Purchase order identifier.

ChiValue.Name: actualPurchaseCost
ChiValue.Notes: The actual purchase cost of this particular asset.

ChiValue.Name: account
ChiValue.Notes: The account to which this actual material item is charged.

ChiValue.Name: quantity
ChiValue.Notes: The quantity of the asset if per unit length, for example conductor.

ChiValue.Name: costDescription
ChiValue.Notes: Description of the cost.

ChiValue.Name: costType
ChiValue.Notes: The category of cost to which this Material Item belongs.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Manhole
ChiNode.Notes: Provides access at key locations to underground cables, equipment, etc. housed inside a protective vault.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Medium
ChiNode.Notes: A substance that either (1) provides the means of transmission of a force or effect, such as hydraulic fluid, or (2) is used for a surrounding or enveloping substance, such as oil in a transformer or circuit breaker.

ChiValue.Name: kind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of this medium.

ChiValue.Name: volumeSpec
ChiValue.Notes: The volume of the medium specified for this application. Note that the actual volume is a type of measurement associated witht the asset.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: OrgAssetRole
ChiNode.Notes: The roles played between an Organisations and an Asset.

ChiValue.Name: percentOwnership
ChiValue.Notes: If the role type is "owner," this indicate the percentage of ownership.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Pole
ChiNode.Notes: A long, slender piece of wood, metal, etc. usually rounded that stands vertically from the ground and is used for mounting various types of overhead equipment. Dimensions of Pole are specified in associated DimensionsInfo.

ChiValue.Name: baseKind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of base for this pole.

ChiValue.Name: preservativeKind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of preservative for this pole.

ChiValue.Name: treatedDate
ChiValue.Notes: Date pole was last treated with preservative.

ChiValue.Name: breastBlock
ChiValue.Notes: True if a block of material has been attached to base of pole in ground for stability. This technique is used primarily when anchors can not be used.

ChiValue.Name: construction
ChiValue.Notes: The framing structure mounted on the pole.

ChiValue.Name: jpaReference
ChiValue.Notes: Joint pole agreement reference number.

ChiValue.Name: treatmentKind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of treatment for this pole.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Procedure
ChiNode.Notes:
A documented procedure for various types of Work or Work Tasks. One or more procedures guide a compatible unit, a standard way of performing a unit of work. The type of procedure is defined in Procedure.type. For example, when type=Inspection, this procedure coupled with Schedule and other information provides the key items of an inspection plan. Another type of Procedure is a Diagnosis. Note that each specific values and settings to be used in a procedure is intended to be described in an instance of ProcedureValue.
A maintenance ticket, a type of Work, is generated whenever maintenance is determined to be needed as a result of an inspection or diagnosis.

ChiValue.Name: corporateCode
ChiValue.Notes: Code for this kind of procedure.

ChiValue.Name: sequenceNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Sequence number in a sequence of procedures being performed.

ChiValue.Name: instruction
ChiValue.Notes: The textual description of the procedure, which references instances of ProcedureValue as appropriate.

ChiValue.Name: kind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of this procedure.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ProcedureDataSet
ChiNode.Notes: A data set recorded each time a procedure is executed. Observed results are captured in associated measurement values and/or values for properties relevant to the type of procedure performed.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: PSRStatus
ChiNode.Notes: The current status of the PowerSystemResource. History of the status is tracked through instances of ActivityRecord.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ReliabilityInfo
ChiNode.Notes: Information regarding the experienced and expected reliability of a specific asset, type of asset, or asset model.

ChiValue.Name: momFailureRate
ChiValue.Notes: Momentary failure rate (temporary failures/kft-year).

ChiValue.Name: mTTR
ChiValue.Notes: Mean time to repair (MTTR - hours).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Specification
ChiNode.Notes: Specification can be used for various purposes relative to an asset, a logical device (PowerSystemResource), location, etc. Examples include documents supplied by manufacturers such as asset installation instructions, asset maintenance instructions, etc.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Structure
ChiNode.Notes: Construction holding assets such as conductors, transformers, switchgear, etc.

ChiValue.Name: height
ChiValue.Notes: Visible height of structure above ground level for overhead construction (e.g., Pole or Tower) or below ground level for an underground vault, manhole, etc. Refer to associated DimensionPropertiesInfo for other types of dimensions.

ChiValue.Name: removeWeed
ChiValue.Notes: True if weeds are to be removed around asset.

ChiValue.Name: weedRemovedDate
ChiValue.Notes: Date weed were last removed.

ChiValue.Name: fumigantName
ChiValue.Notes: Name of fumigant.

ChiValue.Name: fumigantAppliedDate
ChiValue.Notes: Date fumigant was last applied.

ChiValue.Name: materialKind
ChiValue.Notes: Material this structure is made of.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: SubstationAsset
ChiNode.Notes: A grouping of assets such as conductors, transformers, switchgear, etc. When located on the ground surface, it is usually surrounded by some kind of fence with a locked gate. It may also be located inside buildings, in underground vaults, and on structures. Use 'category' for utility-specific categorisation (such as Air Cooled, Gas Insultated, etc.).

ChiValue.Name: function
ChiValue.Notes: Function of this substation asset.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TestDataSet
ChiNode.Notes: Test results, usually obtained by a lab or other independent organisation.

ChiValue.Name: conclusion
ChiValue.Notes: Conclusion drawn from test results.

ChiValue.Name: specimenID
ChiValue.Notes: Identifier of specimen used in inspection or test.

ChiValue.Name: specToLabDate
ChiValue.Notes: The date the specimen was received by the lab.

ChiValue.Name: conclusionDate
ChiValue.Notes: The date the conclusion form the test was issued by the lab.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Tower
ChiNode.Notes: Large structure used to carry transmission lines, subtransmission lines, and/or other equipment/lines (e.g., communication). Dimensions of the Tower are specified in associated DimensionsInfo class.

ChiValue.Name: constructionKind
ChiValue.Notes: Construction structure on the tower.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TransformerObservation
ChiNode.Notes: Common information captured during transformer inspections and/or diagrnotics. Note that some properties may be measured through other means and therefore have measurement values in addition to the observed values recorded here.

ChiValue.Name: dga
ChiValue.Notes: Dissolved Gas Analysis. Typical values are: Acceptable, Overheating, Corona, Sparking, Arcing.

ChiValue.Name: waterContent
ChiValue.Notes: Water Content expressed in parts per million.

ChiValue.Name: oilColor
ChiValue.Notes: Oil Quality Analysis-Color.

ChiValue.Name: oilDielectricStrength
ChiValue.Notes: Oil Quality Analysis-Dielectric Strength.

ChiValue.Name: oilNeutralizationNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Oil Quality Analysis-Neutralization Number - Number - Mg KOH.

ChiValue.Name: oilIFT
ChiValue.Notes: Oil Quality Analysis- inter facial tension (IFT) - number-Dynes/CM.

ChiValue.Name: hotSpotTemp
ChiValue.Notes: Hotspot oil temperature.

ChiValue.Name: topOilTemp
ChiValue.Notes: Top oil temperature.

ChiValue.Name: bushingTemp
ChiValue.Notes: Bushing temperature.

ChiValue.Name: pumpVibration
ChiValue.Notes: Pump vibration, with typical values being: nominal, high.

ChiValue.Name: oilLevel
ChiValue.Notes: The level of oil in the transformer.

ChiValue.Name: freqResp
ChiValue.Notes: Frequency Response Analysis. Typical values are: acceptable, slight movement, significant movement, failed, near failure. A graphic of the response diagram, which is a type of document, may be associated with this analysis through the recursive document relationship of the ProcedureDataSet.

ChiValue.Name: furfuralDP
ChiValue.Notes: Overall measure of furfural in oil and mechanical strength of paper. DP, the degree of polymerization, is the strength of the paper. Furfural is a measure of furfural compounds, often expressed in parts per million.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: UndergroundStructure
ChiNode.Notes: Abstract class for underground structures. Typical structure types are: BURD, Enclosure, Hand Hole, Manhole, Pad/Slab, Subsurface Enclosure, Trench, Tunnel, Vault, Pull/Splice Box.

ChiValue.Name: sealingDate
ChiValue.Notes: Date vault was sealed.

ChiValue.Name: sealingWarrantyExpires
ChiValue.Notes: Date sealing warranty expires.

ChiValue.Name: material
ChiValue.Notes: Primary material of underground structure.

ChiValue.Name: ventilation
ChiValue.Notes: True if vault is ventilating.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: WindingInsulation

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: PowerRating
ChiNode.Notes:
There are often stages of power which are associated with stages of cooling. For instance, a transformer may be rated 121kV on the primary, 15kV on the secondary and 4kV on the tertiary winding. These are voltage ratings and the power ratings are generally the same for all three windings and independent of the voltage ratings, there are instances where the tertiary may have a lower power rating.
For example, for three stages, the power rating may be 15/20/25 MVA and the cooling is OA/FA/FOA. The 15 MVA rating goes with the OA cooling (Oil and Air cooling). This is called the self cooled rating as there are no external cooling enhancements. The 20 MVA rating goes with the FA cooling (Forced Air cooling), this means that when the fans are running and thus enhancing the cooling characteristics, the transformer can operate at a power level of 20 MVA. The 25 MVA rating goes with the FOA cooling (Forced Oil and Air cooling), this means that when the fans and pumps are running and thus enhancing the cooling characteristics even more than before, the transformer can operate at a power level of 25 MVA. This 15/20/25 MVA does not state how the power is split between the various windings. It may be 25 MVA input on the primary, 25 MVA output on the secondary and 0 MVA output on the tertiary. It may also operate at 25 MVA input on the primary, 17 MVA output on the secondary and 8 MVA output on the tertiary.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CustomerBillingInfo
ChiNode.Notes:
The creation of the monthly customer billing statements is the method employed to notify Customers of charges, adjustments and credits applied to their account for Services and Products. The actuall billing occurs through an ErpInvoice. The CustomerBillingInfo includes information from the payment, collection, meter reading, installed meter, service, site, customer, customer account, customer agreement, services and pricing subject areas. Each component price shows up as a separate line item on the ErpInvoice.
The Customer Billing Statement may include collection and account messages, marketing/civic event messages and bill inserts.
One Customer Billing Statement is produced for all Agreements under a CustomerAccount per billing cycle date defined in 'CustomerAccount.billingCycle'.
The history of CustomerBillingInfo, Invoices and Payments is to be maintained in associated ActivityRecords.

ChiValue.Name: billingDate

ChiValue.Name: kind

ChiValue.Name: dueDate
ChiValue.Notes: Calculated date upon which a customer billing amount is due, used in the invoicing process to determine when a Customer's Payment is delinquent. It takes into consideration the regulatory criteria and the Customer's requested due date. In the absence of a Customer requested due date, the due date is typically calculated from the regulated number of days and the 'billingDate'.

ChiValue.Name: outBalance
ChiValue.Notes: Outstanding balance on the CustomerAccount as of the statement date.

ChiValue.Name: pymtPlanAmt
ChiValue.Notes: Monthly amortized amount due during each billing cycle for the CustomerAccount balance for which the Payment Plan is set-up.

ChiValue.Name: pymtPlanType
ChiValue.Notes: Type of payment plan.

ChiValue.Name: lastPaymentDate
ChiValue.Notes: Date of the last payment received from the customer. It is retained in the Customer Billing system, although the details of each payment are tracked in the ERP system.

ChiValue.Name: lastPaymentAmt
ChiValue.Notes: Amount of the last payment received from the customer. It is retained in the Customer Billing system, although the details of each payment are tracked in the ERP system.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ExternalCustomerAgreement
ChiNode.Notes: A type of customer agreement involving an external agency. For example, a customer may form a contracts with an Energy Service Supplier if Direct Access is permitted.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: OutageHistory
ChiNode.Notes: A document collecting OutageReports, that allows utilities to examine the number of outages suffered by a customer. Also provides data to calculate the total supply interruption to any customer over a given period.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: PhaseLoad
ChiNode.Notes: Model's load with the unified characteristics. It can be one phase of a multi-phase load and also can be a three-phase load with unified characteristics. The aggregate relationship between DistributionLoad and PhaseLoad allows a distribution load to have any type configuration like single phase, two-phase or three-phase.

ChiValue.Name: pConstantCurrentPct
ChiValue.Notes: Percentage of the active power of the load which has constant current.

ChiValue.Name: pConstantImpedancePct
ChiValue.Notes: Percentage of the active power of the load which has constant impedance.

ChiValue.Name: pConstantPowerPct
ChiValue.Notes: Percentage of the active power of the load which is constant.

ChiValue.Name: qConstantPowerPct
ChiValue.Notes: Percentage of the reactive power of the load which is constant.

ChiValue.Name: qConstantCurrentPct
ChiValue.Notes: Percentage of the reactive power of the load which has constant current.

ChiValue.Name: qConstantImpedancePct
ChiValue.Notes: Percentage of the reactive power of the load which has constant impedance.

ChiValue.Name: pVoltDependanceFactor
ChiValue.Notes: Voltage dependence of the active part of the pConstantCurrentPct.

ChiValue.Name: qVoltDependanceFactor
ChiValue.Notes: Voltage dependence of the reactive part of the qConstantCurrentPct.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: PowerQualityPricing
ChiNode.Notes: Pricing can be based on power quality.

ChiValue.Name: emergencyHighVoltLimit
ChiValue.Notes: Emergency high voltage limit.

ChiValue.Name: emergencyLowVoltLimit
ChiValue.Notes: Emergency low voltage limit.

ChiValue.Name: normalHighVoltLimit
ChiValue.Notes: Normal high voltage limit.

ChiValue.Name: normalLowVoltLimit
ChiValue.Notes: Normal low voltage limit.

ChiValue.Name: powerFactorMin
ChiValue.Notes: Threshold minimum power factor for this PricingStructure, specified in instances where a special charge is levied if the actual power factor for a Service falls below the value specified here.

ChiValue.Name: valueUninterruptedServiceEnergy
ChiValue.Notes: Value of uninterrupted service (Cost per energy).

ChiValue.Name: valueUninterruptedServiceP
ChiValue.Notes: Value of uninterrupted service (Cost per active power).

ChiValue.Name: voltImbalanceViolCost
ChiValue.Notes: Voltage imbalance violation cost (Cost per unit Voltage).

ChiValue.Name: voltLimitViolCost
ChiValue.Notes: Voltage limit violation cost (Cost per unit Voltage).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ServiceGuarantee
ChiNode.Notes:
A service guarantee, often imposed by a regulator, defines conditions that, if not satisfied, will result in the utility making a monetary payment to the customer. Note that guarantee's identifier is in the 'name' attribute and the status of the guarantee is in the 'Status.status' attribute.
Example service requirements include:
1) If power is not restored within 24 hours, customers can claim $50 for residential customers or $100 for commercial and industrial customers. In addition for each extra period of 12 hours the customer's supply has not been activated, the customer can claim $25.
2) If a customer has a question about their electricity bill, the utility will investigate and respond to the inquiry within 15 working days. If utility fails to meet its guarantee, utility will automatically pay the customer $50.

ChiValue.Name: payAmount
ChiValue.Notes: The amount to be paid by the service provider to the customer for each vilations of the 'service Requirement'.

ChiValue.Name: automaticPay
ChiValue.Notes: True if utility must autmatically pay the specified amount whenever the condition is not satisified, otherwise customer must make a claim to receive payment.

ChiValue.Name: endDate
ChiValue.Notes: The end of the period in which this service guantee applies.

ChiValue.Name: serviceRequirement
ChiValue.Notes: Explanation of the requirement and conditions for satisfying it.

ChiValue.Name: startDate
ChiValue.Notes: The beginning of the period in which this service guantee applies.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: StandardIndustryCode
ChiNode.Notes:
The Standard Industrial Classification (SIC) are the codes that identify the type of products/service an industry is involved in, and used for statutory reporting purposes. For example, in the USA these codes are located by the federal government, and then published in a book entitled "The Standard Industrial Classification Manual". The codes are arranged in a hierarchical structure.
Note that Residential Service Agreements are not classified according to the SIC codes.

ChiValue.Name: code
ChiValue.Notes: Standard alphanumeric code assigned to a particular product/service within an industry.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: SubscribePowerCurve
ChiNode.Notes: Price curve for specifying the cost of energy (X) at points in time (y1) according to a prcing structure, which is based on a tariff.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: WorkBillingInfo
ChiNode.Notes: Billing information for work performed for the customer. The history of Work Billing Info, Invoices, and Payments is to be maintained in associated ActivityRecords.

ChiValue.Name: dueDate
ChiValue.Notes: Date by which payment for bill is expected from client.

ChiValue.Name: issueDate
ChiValue.Notes: Date bill was issued to client.

ChiValue.Name: receivedDate
ChiValue.Notes: Date payment was received from client.

ChiValue.Name: workPrice
ChiValue.Notes: Amount of bill.

ChiValue.Name: costEstimate
ChiValue.Notes: Estimated cost for work.

ChiValue.Name: deposit
ChiValue.Notes: Amount of price on deposit.

ChiValue.Name: discount
ChiValue.Notes: Discount from standard price.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: DocErpPersonRole
ChiNode.Notes: Roles played between Persons and Documents.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: DocOrgRole
ChiNode.Notes: Roles played between Organisations and Documents.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpBankAccount
ChiNode.Notes:
Relationship under a particular name, usually evidenced by a deposit against which withdrawals can be made. Types of bank accounts include: demand, time, custodial, joint, trustee, corporate, special, and regular accounts.
A statement of transactions during a fiscal period and the resulting balance is maintained on each account.
For Payment metering, the account is associated with Bank and Supplier, reflecting details of the bank account used for depositing revenue collected by TokenVendor. The name of the account holder should be specified in 'name' attribute.

ChiValue.Name: bankABA
ChiValue.Notes: Bank ABA.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpBOM
ChiNode.Notes:
Information that generally describes the Bill of Material Structure and its contents for a utility.
This is used by ERP systems to transfer Bill of Material information between two business applications.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpBomItemData
ChiNode.Notes: An individual item on a bill of materials.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpChartOfAccounts
ChiNode.Notes: Accounting structure of a business. Each account represents a financial aspect of a business, such as its Accounts Payable, or the value of its inventory, or its office supply expenses.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpCompetency
ChiNode.Notes: Information that describes aptitudes of a utility employee. Unlike Skills that an ErpPerson must be certified to perform before undertaking certain type of assignments (to be able to perfrom a Craft), ErpCompetency has more to do with typical Human Resource (HR) matters such as schooling, training, etc.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpEngChangeOrder
ChiNode.Notes: General Utility Engineering Change Order information.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpInventory
ChiNode.Notes: Utility inventory-related information about an item or part (and not for description of the item and its attributes). It is used by ERP applications to enable the synchronization of Inventory data that exists on separate Item Master databases. This data is not the master data that describes the attributes of the item such as dimensions, weight, or unit of measure - it describes the item as it exists at a specific location.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpInventoryCount
ChiNode.Notes:
This is related to Inventory physical counts organized by AssetModel. Note that a count of a type of asset can be accomplished by the association inherited by AssetModel (from Document) to Asset.
It enables ERP applications to transfer an inventory count between ERP and the actual physical inventory location. This count may be a cycle count or a physical count.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpInvoice
ChiNode.Notes: A roll up of invoice line items. The whole invoice has a due date and amount to be paid, with information such as customer, banks etc. being obtained through associations. The invoice roll up is based on individual line items that each contain amounts and descriptions for specific services or products.

ChiValue.Name: billMediaKind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of media by which the CustomerBillingInfo was delivered.

ChiValue.Name: referenceNumber
ChiValue.Notes: The number of an invoice to be reference by this invoice.

ChiValue.Name: amount
ChiValue.Notes: Total amount due on this invoice based on line items and applicable adjustments.

ChiValue.Name: dueDate
ChiValue.Notes: Calculated date upon which the Invoice amount is due.

ChiValue.Name: mailedDate
ChiValue.Notes: Date on which the customer billing statement/invoice was printed/mailed.

ChiValue.Name: kind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of invoice (default is 'sales').

ChiValue.Name: transferType
ChiValue.Notes: The type of invoice transfer.

ChiValue.Name: transactionDate
ChiValue.Notes: The date of which the invoice is issued.

ChiValue.Name: proForma
ChiValue.Notes: True if payment is to be paid by a Customer to accept a particular ErpQuote (with associated Design) and have work initiated, at which time an associated ErpInvoice should automatically be generated. EprPayment.subjectStatus satisfies terms specificed in the ErpQuote.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpInvoiceLineItem
ChiNode.Notes: An individual line item on an invoice.

ChiValue.Name: lineNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Line item number on invoice statement.

ChiValue.Name: lineAmount
ChiValue.Notes: The amount due for this line item.

ChiValue.Name: dateGL
ChiValue.Notes: Date line item will be posted to the General Ledger.

ChiValue.Name: kind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of line item.

ChiValue.Name: start
ChiValue.Notes: The start of a bill period for the line item.

ChiValue.Name: end
ChiValue.Notes: The end of a bill period for the line item.

ChiValue.Name: lineVersion
ChiValue.Notes: The version number of the bill run.

ChiValue.Name: previousAmount
ChiValue.Notes: The previous line item charge amount.

ChiValue.Name: netAmount
ChiValue.Notes: The net line item charge amount.

ChiValue.Name: accountGL
ChiValue.Notes: GL account code, must be a valid combination.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpIssueInventory
ChiNode.Notes: Can be used to request an application to process an issue or request information about an issue.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpItemMaster
ChiNode.Notes:
Any unique purchased part for manufactured product tracked by ERP systems for a utility.
Item, as used by the OAG, refers to the basic information about an item, including its attributes, cost, and locations. It does not include item quantities. Compare to the Inventory, which includes all quantities and other location-specific information.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpJournal
ChiNode.Notes:
Book for recording accounting transactions as they occur. Transactions and adjustments are first recorded in a journal, which is like a diary of instructions, advising which account to be charged and by how much.
A journal represents a change in the balances of a business's financial accounts. Many tasks or transactions throughout an enterprise will result in the creation of a journal. Some examples are creating a customer invoice, paying a vendor, transferring inventory, or paying employees.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpJournalEntry
ChiNode.Notes: Details of an individual entry in a journal, which is to be posted to a ledger on the posting date.

ChiValue.Name: accountID
ChiValue.Notes: Account identifier for this entry.

ChiValue.Name: amount
ChiValue.Notes: The amount of the debit or credit for this account.

ChiValue.Name: postingDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time this entry is to be posted to the ledger.

ChiValue.Name: transactionDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time journal entry was recorded.

ChiValue.Name: sourceID
ChiValue.Notes: The identifer of the source for this entry.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpLedBudLineItem
ChiNode.Notes: Individual entry of a given Ledger Budget, typically containing information such as amount, accounting date, accounting period, and is associated with the applicable general ledger account.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpLedger
ChiNode.Notes: In accounting transactions, a ledger is a book containing accounts to which debits and credits are posted from journals, where transactions are initially recorded.
