Journal entries are periodically posted to the ledger. Ledger Actual represents actual amounts by account within ledger within company or business area. Actual amounts may be generated in a source application and then loaded to a specific ledger within the enterprise general ledger or budget application.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpLedgerBudget
ChiNode.Notes: Information for utility Ledger Budgets. They support the transfer budget amounts between all possible source applications throughout an enterprise and a general ledger or budget application.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpLedgerEntry
ChiNode.Notes: Details of an individual entry in a ledger, which was posted from a journal on the posted date.

ChiValue.Name: accountID
ChiValue.Notes: Account identifier for this entry.

ChiValue.Name: accountKind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of account for this entry.

ChiValue.Name: amount
ChiValue.Notes: The amount of the debit or credit for this account.

ChiValue.Name: postedDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time this entry was posted to the ledger.

ChiValue.Name: transactionDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time journal entry was recorded.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpOrganisation
ChiNode.Notes: Identifies organisations that might have roles as utilities, contractors, suppliers, manufacturers, customers, etc. Organisations may also have parent-child relationships to identify departments within an organisation, or parent company relationships. The organization may be internal (e.g., departments) or external to the utility. There may be multiple organizations of a given 'category', each with a unique 'code'. Identifies organisations that might have roles as utilities, contractors, suppliers, manufacturers, customers, etc. Organisations may also have parent-child relationships to identify departments within an organisation, or parent company relationships. The organization may be internal (e.g., departments) or external to the utility. There may be multiple organizations of a given 'category', each with a unique 'code'.

ChiValue.Name: category
ChiValue.Notes: Category by utility's corporate standards and practices.

ChiValue.Name: code
ChiValue.Notes: Designated code for organisation.

ChiValue.Name: isCostCenter
ChiValue.Notes: True if organisation is cost center.

ChiValue.Name: isProfitCenter
ChiValue.Notes: True if organisation is profit center.

ChiValue.Name: mode
ChiValue.Notes: Operational mode of the organisation, often required for outage reporting purposes. Some utilities use text to describe various modes (like nominal, emergency, storm, other), while others use severity ratings (for example, 0 is a nominal condition and 5 is the most severe condition).

ChiValue.Name: optOut
ChiValue.Notes: True if organisation "opted out", i.e., has requested that their contact information not be shared with other organisations for purposes of solicitation.

ChiValue.Name: governmentID
ChiValue.Notes: Unique identifier for organisation relative to its governing authority, for example a federal tax identifier.

ChiValue.Name: industryID
ChiValue.Notes: Unique identifier for a given organisation (business). In the USA, this is a 'Dunns" or DB number. This identifier is typically in addition to the identifiers that organizations assign (on an internal basis) to each of their locations. Note that a unique identifier can be set up for each location of an organisation. This requirement is supported through the recursive Organisation-Organisation relationship, where each child Organisation can have a specified physical location.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpPayable
ChiNode.Notes: A transaction that represents an invoice from a supplier. A payable (or voucher) is an open item, approved and ready for payment, in the Accounts Payable ledger.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpPayableLineItem
ChiNode.Notes: Of an ErpPayable, a line item references an ErpInvoiceLineitem or other source such as credit memos.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpPayment
ChiNode.Notes: Payment infromation and status for any individual line item of an ErpInvoice (e.g., when payment is from a customer). ErpPayable is also updated when payment is to a supplier and ErpReceivable is updated when payment is from a customer. Multiple payments can be made against a single line item and an individual payment can apply to more that one line item.

ChiValue.Name: termsPayment
ChiValue.Notes: Payment terms (e.g., net 30).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpPerson
ChiNode.Notes: General purpose information for name and other information to contact people.

ChiValue.Name: firstName
ChiValue.Notes: Person's first name.

ChiValue.Name: lastName
ChiValue.Notes: Person's last (family, sir) name.

ChiValue.Name: mName
ChiValue.Notes: Middle name(s) or initial(s).

ChiValue.Name: specialNeed
ChiValue.Notes: Special service needs for the person (contact) are described; examples include life support, etc.

ChiValue.Name: governmentID
ChiValue.Notes: Unique identifier for person relative to its governing authority, for example a federal tax identifier (such as a Social Security number in the United States).

ChiValue.Name: prefix
ChiValue.Notes: A prefix or title for the person's name, such as Miss, Mister, Doctor, etc.

ChiValue.Name: suffix
ChiValue.Notes: A suffix for the person's name, such as II, III, etc.

ChiValue.Name: category
ChiValue.Notes:
Category of this person relative to utility operations, classified according to the utility's corporate standards and practices. Examples include employee, contractor, agent, not affiliated, etc.
Note that this field is not used to indicate whether this person is a customer of the utility. Often an employee or contractor is also a customer. Customer information is gained with relationship to Organisation and CustomerData. In similar fashion, this field does not indicate the various roles this person may fill as part of utility operations.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpPersonnel
ChiNode.Notes: Information that applies to the basic data about a utility person, used by ERP applications to transfer Personnel data for a worker.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpPOLineItem
ChiNode.Notes: Of an ErpPurchaseOrder, this is an individually ordered item or product along with the quantity, price and other descriptive information.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpProjectAccounting
ChiNode.Notes: Utility Project Accounting information, used by ERP applications to enable all relevant sub-systems that submit single sided transactions to transfer information with a Project Accounting Application. This would include, but not necessarily be limited to: Accounts Payable, Accounts Receivable, Budget, Order Management, Purchasing, Time and Labor, Travel and Expense.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpPurchaseOrder
ChiNode.Notes: A document that communicates an order to purchase goods from a buyer to a supplier. The PurchaseOrder carries information to and from the buyer and supplier. It is a legally binding document once both Parties agree to the contents and the specified terms and conditions of the order.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpQuote
ChiNode.Notes: Document describing the prices of goods or services provided by a supplier. It includes the terms of the purchase, delivery proposals, identification of goods or services ordered, as well as their quantities.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpQuoteLineItem
ChiNode.Notes: Of an ErpQuote, the item or product quoted along with quantity, price and other descriptive information.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpRecDelvLineItem
ChiNode.Notes: Of an ErpReceiveDelivery, this is an individually received good or service by the Organisation receiving goods or services. It may be used to indicate receipt of goods in conjunction with a purchase order line item.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpReceivable
ChiNode.Notes: Transaction representing an invoice, credit memo or debit memo to a customer. It is an open (unpaid) item in the Accounts Receivable ledger.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpReceiveDelivery
ChiNode.Notes: Transaction for an Organisation receiving goods or services that may be used to indicate receipt of goods in conjunction with a purchase order. A receivable is an open (unpaid) item in the Accounts Receivable ledger.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpRecLineItem
ChiNode.Notes: Individual entry of an ErpReceivable, it is a particular transaction representing an invoice, credit memo or debit memo to a customer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpReqLineItem
ChiNode.Notes: Information that describes a requested item and its attributes.

ChiValue.Name: quantity
ChiValue.Notes: Quantity of item requisitioned.

ChiValue.Name: cost
ChiValue.Notes: Cost of material

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpRequisition
ChiNode.Notes: General information that applies to a utility requisition that is a request for the purchase of goods or services. Typically, a requisition leads to the creation of a purchase order to a specific supplier.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpSalesOrder
ChiNode.Notes:
General purpose Sales Order is used for utility service orders, etc.
As used by the OAG, the SalesOrder is a step beyond a PurchaseOrder in that the receiving entity of the order also communicates SalesInformoration about the Order along with the Order itself.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpSiteLevelData
ChiNode.Notes: For a utility, general information that describes physical locations of organizations or the location codes and their meanings. This enables ERP applications to ensure that the physical location identifiers are synchronized between the business applications.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpTelephoneNumber
ChiNode.Notes: The telephone number for a person or organisation.

ChiValue.Name: usage
ChiValue.Notes: The purpose of the telephone: home, mobile, home fax, office, office fax, switchboard, other.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpTimeEntry
ChiNode.Notes: An individual entry on an ErpTimeSheet.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpTimeSheet
ChiNode.Notes: Time sheet for employees and contractors. Note that ErpTimeSheet inherits the relationship to ErpPerson from Document.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: OrgErpPersonRole
ChiNode.Notes: Roles played between Persons and Organisations.

ChiValue.Name: clientID
ChiValue.Notes: Identifiers of the person held by an organisation, such as a government agency (federal, state, province, city, county), financial institutions, etc.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: OrgOrgRole
ChiNode.Notes:
Roles played between Organisations and other Organisations. This includes role ups for ogranisations, cost centers, profit centers, regulatory reporting, etc.
Note that the parent and child relationship is indicated by the name on each end of the association.

ChiValue.Name: clientID
ChiValue.Notes: Identifiers of the organisation held by another organisation, such as a government agency (federal, state, province, city, county), financial institution (Dun and Bradstreet), etc.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlBaseSymbol
ChiNode.Notes: Allows referencing and extension of external symbols, which may be stored in a symbol repository. The graphical properties from a referenced external symbol override the ones read in from the base symbol.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlColour
ChiNode.Notes: The solid color that will be used. The color value is RGB-encoded using two hexadecimal digits per primary-color component, in the order Red, Green, Blue, prefixed with a hash (#) sign. The hexadecimal digits between A and F may be in either uppercase or lowercase. For example, full red is encoded as "#ff0000" (with no quotation marks). If the Stroke cssParameter element is absent, the default color is defined to be black ("#000000").

ChiValue.Name: green
ChiValue.Notes: The color value for GREEN (RGB-encoded using two hexadecimal digits per primary-color component, in the order Red, Green, Blue, prefixed with a hash (#) sign.)

ChiValue.Name: blue
ChiValue.Notes: The color value for BLUE (RGB-encoded using two hexadecimal digits per primary-color component, in the order Red, Green, Blue, prefixed with a hash (#) sign.).

ChiValue.Name: red
ChiValue.Notes: The color value for RED (RGB-encoded using two hexadecimal digits per primary-color component, in the order Red, Green, Blue, prefixed with a hash (#) sign.)

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlCoordinateSystem
ChiNode.Notes: A coordinate reference system consists of a set of coordinate system axes that is related to the earth through a datum that defines the size and shape of the earth or some abstract reference system such as those used for rendering schemantic diagrams, internal views of items such as cabinets, vaults, etc. Geometries in GML indicate the coordinate reference system in which their measurements have been made.

ChiValue.Name: xMin
ChiValue.Notes: The minimum position allowed along the X axis of the coordinate reference system.

ChiValue.Name: yMin
ChiValue.Notes: The minimum position allowed along the Y axis of the coordinate reference system.

ChiValue.Name: xMax
ChiValue.Notes: The maximum position allowed along the X axis of the coordinate reference system.

ChiValue.Name: yMax
ChiValue.Notes: The maximum position allowed along the Y axis of the coordinate reference system.

ChiValue.Name: zMin
ChiValue.Notes: If applicable, the minimum position allowed along the Z axis of the coordinate reference system.

ChiValue.Name: zMax
ChiValue.Notes: If applicable, the maximum position allowed along the Z axis of the coordinate reference system.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlDiagramObject
ChiNode.Notes: Any of the magnitudes that serve to define the position of a point by reference to a fixed figure, system of lines, etc.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlFeatureStyle
ChiNode.Notes: Used for styling a particular aspect or aspects of a feature, such as geometry, topology or arbitrary text string.

ChiValue.Name: semanticTypeIdentifier
ChiValue.Notes: The SemanticTypeIdentifier is experimental in GML and is intended to be used to identify what the feature style is suitable to be used for using community-controlled name(s). For example, a single style may be suitable to use with many different feature types.

ChiValue.Name: queryGrammar
ChiValue.Notes: Grammar used in the content of the gml:featureConstraint element.

ChiValue.Name: featureConstraint
ChiValue.Notes: This property is used to further constrain the feature instance set to which the style applies. It is optional and its value is an XPath expression. If the property does not exist, the style applies to all feature instances selected by 'featureType' or 'baseType'.

ChiValue.Name: featureTypeName
ChiValue.Notes: Identifies the specific feature type that the feature-type style is for.

ChiValue.Name: featureType
ChiValue.Notes: The simplest and most common way of relating features and styles is by using this attribute. Its value will be the declared name of a feature, instances of which we want to style. For example, if the featureType = Switch, this FeatureStyle object will simply apply to all Switch features.

ChiValue.Name: baseType
ChiValue.Notes: Another way of selecting the feature instances to which the style applies is to specify, as the value of this attribute, the name of the base type from which feature or features derive.

ChiValue.Name: version
ChiValue.Notes: Allows version numbers to be identified when the SLD pieces are used independently.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlFeatureType
ChiNode.Notes: Type classification of feature.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlFill
ChiNode.Notes: Specifies how the area of the geometry will be filled.

ChiValue.Name: opacity
ChiValue.Notes:
Specifies the level of translucency to use when rendering the Fill. The value is encoded as a floating-point value
between 0.0 and 1.0 with 0.0 representing completely transparent and 1.0 representing completely opaque, with a linear scale of translucency for intermediate values. The default value is 1.0

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlFont
ChiNode.Notes: Identifies a font of a certain family, style, and size.

ChiValue.Name: family
ChiValue.Notes: Family name of a font to use. Allowed values are system-dependent. Any number of font-family attributes may be given and they are assumed to be in preferred order.

ChiValue.Name: style
ChiValue.Notes: The style to use for a font. The allowed values are "normal", "italic", and "oblique".

ChiValue.Name: weight
ChiValue.Notes: The amount of weight or boldness to use for a font. Allowed values are "normal" and "bold".

ChiValue.Name: size
ChiValue.Notes: The size to use for the font in pixels. The default is defined to be 10 pixels, though various systems may have restrictions on what sizes are available.

ChiValue.Name: absoluteSize
ChiValue.Notes: True if "size" is expressed in absolute values. Default is false.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlGeometryStyle
ChiNode.Notes: The style for one geometry of a feature. Any number of geometry style descriptors can be assigned to one feature style. This is usually required for features with multiple geometry properties.

ChiValue.Name: geometryProperty
ChiValue.Notes: The name of the geometry property of a feature to which this GeometryStyle applies.

ChiValue.Name: geometryType
ChiValue.Notes: It is necessary to specify the geometry type using this attribute as well since the application schema of the geometry property may allow different geometries as its value.

ChiValue.Name: symbol
ChiValue.Notes: Graphical symbol used to render a geometry or a topology. A symbol is a description of graphical attributes of a graphical object without a particular, implicit meaning. It can be a description of a line, circle, polygon or more complex drawing.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlGraphic
ChiNode.Notes: A "graphic symbol" with an inherent shape, color(s), and possibly size. A "graphic" can be very informally defined as "a little picture" and can be of either a raster or vector-graphic source type.

ChiValue.Name: opacity
ChiValue.Notes:
Specifies the level of translucency to use when rendering the Graphic.The value is encoded as a floating-point value
between 0.0 and 1.0 with 0.0 representing completely transparent and 1.0 representing completely opaque, with a linear scale of translucency for intermediate values. The default value is 1.0

ChiValue.Name: size
ChiValue.Notes: Gives the absolute size of the graphic in pixels encoded as a floatingpoint number. The default size for an object is context-dependent. Negative values are not allowed.

ChiValue.Name: minSize
ChiValue.Notes: The minimum symbol size allowed.

ChiValue.Name: rotation
ChiValue.Notes: Gives the rotation of a graphic in the clockwise direction about its center point in decimal degrees, encoded as a floating-point number. Negative values mean counter-clockwise rotation. The default value is 0.0 (no rotation). Note that there is no connection between source geometry types and rotations; the point used for plotting has no inherent direction. Also, the point within the graphic about which it is rotated is format dependent. If a format does not include an inherent rotation point, then the point of rotation should be the centroid.

ChiValue.Name: xScale
ChiValue.Notes: Horizontal scaling factor of normal symbol - particularly applicable to busbars if not described through a sequence of gmlPositions (e.g., Busbar).

ChiValue.Name: yScale
ChiValue.Notes: Vertical scaling factor of normal symbol - particularly applicable to busbars if not described through a sequence of gmlPositions (e.g., Busbars).

ChiValue.Name: symbolID
ChiValue.Notes: The identifier of the symbol, if not derived from the type of CIM object (PSR, Asset, Organisation, Document, etc.) gmlSymbolPlacement is associated with.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlHalo
ChiNode.Notes: A type of Fill that is applied to the backgrounds of font glyphs. The use of halos greatly improves the readability of text labels.

ChiValue.Name: opacity
ChiValue.Notes:
Specifies the level of translucency to use when rendering the Fill. The value is encoded as a floating-point value
between 0.0 and 1.0 with 0.0 representing completely transparent and 1.0 representing completely opaque, with a linear scale of translucency for intermediate values. The default value is 1.0

ChiValue.Name: radius
ChiValue.Notes: The Radius element gives the absolute size of a halo radius in pixels encoded as a floating-point number. The radius is taken from the outside edge of a font glyph to extend the area of coverage of the glyph (and the inside edge of ?holes? in the glyphs). The default radius is one pixel. Negative values are not allowed.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlLabelPlacement
ChiNode.Notes: Used to position a label relative to a point or a line.

ChiValue.Name: displacementX
ChiValue.Notes: X displacement from the main-geometry point to render a text label.

ChiValue.Name: displacementY
ChiValue.Notes: Y displacement from the main-geometry point to render a text label.

ChiValue.Name: anchorX
ChiValue.Notes: X-coordinate location inside of a label to use for anchoring the label to the main-geometry point.

ChiValue.Name: anchorY
ChiValue.Notes: Y-coordinate location inside of a label to use for anchoring the label to the main-geometry point.

ChiValue.Name: rotation
ChiValue.Notes: Clockwise rotation of the label in degrees from the normal direction for a font.

ChiValue.Name: offset
ChiValue.Notes: Perpendicular distance away from a line to draw a label. The distance is in pixels and is positive to the left-hand side of the line string. Negative numbers mean right. The default offset is 0.

ChiValue.Name: type
ChiValue.Notes: Type of "LabelPlacement" which in turn specifies where and how a text label should be rendered relative to a geometry.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlLabelStyle
ChiNode.Notes: The style for the text that is to be displayed along with the graphical representation of a feature. The content of the label is not necessarily defined in the GML data set. More precisely, the content can be static text specified in the style itself and the text from the GML data set. Label style has two elements: gml:style that specifies the style and gml:label that is used to compose the label content.

ChiValue.Name: labelExpression
ChiValue.Notes: Allows both text content and unbounded number of gml:LabelExpression elements. The value of gml:LabelExpression element is an XPath expression that selects the value of some property of the feature.

ChiValue.Name: style
ChiValue.Notes: Used to specify the style of the rendered text. The CSS2 styling expressions grammar should be used to express graphic properties.

ChiValue.Name: transform
ChiValue.Notes: Allows us to specify a transformation expression that will be applied to the symbol in the rendering phase. Its type is xsd:string and the value is specified in the SVG specification (transform attribute).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlLineGeometry
ChiNode.Notes: Typically used for rendering linear assets and/or power system resources.

ChiValue.Name: sourceSide
ChiValue.Notes: For dynamic network update (i.e. colouring) purposes

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlLineSymbol
ChiNode.Notes: Used to style a "stroke" along a linear geometry type, such as a string of line segments.

ChiValue.Name: sourceSide
ChiValue.Notes: For dynamic network update (i.e. colouring) purposes

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlMark
ChiNode.Notes: Defines a "shape" which has coloring applied to it (i.e. square, circle, triangle, star, ...).

ChiValue.Name: wellKnownName
ChiValue.Notes:
Gives the well-known name of the shape of the mark.
Allowed values include at least square, circle, triangle, star, cross, and x.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlObservation
ChiNode.Notes: A GML observation models the act of observing, often with a camera, a person or some form of instrument. An observation feature describes the "metadata" associated with an information capture event, together with a value for the result of the observation. The basic structures introduced in this class are intended to serve as the foundation for more comprehensive schemas for scientific, technical and engineering measurement schemas.

ChiValue.Name: using
ChiValue.Notes: Contains or points to a description of a sensor, instrument or procedure used for the observation.

ChiValue.Name: target
ChiValue.Notes: Contains or points to the specimen, region or station which is the object of the observation

ChiValue.Name: resultOf
ChiValue.Notes: Indicates the result of the observation.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlPointGeometry
ChiNode.Notes: Typically used for rendering power system resources and/or point assets.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlPointSymbol
ChiNode.Notes: Used to draw a "graphic" at a point.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlPolygonGeometry
ChiNode.Notes: Used to show the footprint of substations, sites, service territories, tax districts, school districts, etc.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlPolygonSymbol
ChiNode.Notes: Used to draw a polygon (or other area-type geometries), including filling its interior and stroking its border (outline).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlPosition
ChiNode.Notes: Position described by a single set of coordinates within a coordinate reference system. Note that a sequence of x/y coordinate pairs may be specified to provide the physical location of non-point oriented objects like Cables, Ducts, etc. or for describing an area of an object like a substation or geographical zone.

ChiValue.Name: sequenceNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Position of this position within a series of positions. It is zero relative.

ChiValue.Name: xPosition
ChiValue.Notes: The position along the X axis of the coordinate reference system.

ChiValue.Name: yPosition
ChiValue.Notes: The position along the Y axis of the coordinate reference system.

ChiValue.Name: zPosition
ChiValue.Notes: If applicable, the position along the Z axis of the coordinate reference system.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlRasterSymbol
ChiNode.Notes: Describes how to render raster/matrix-coverage data (e.g., satellite photos, DEMs).

ChiValue.Name: opacity
ChiValue.Notes: Specifies the level of translucency to use when rendering the Graphic. The value is encoded as a floating-point value between 0.0 and 1.0 with 0.0 representing completely transparent and 1.0 representing completely opaque, with a linear scale of translucency for intermediate values. The default value is 1.0.

ChiValue.Name: overlapbehaviour
ChiValue.Notes: Tells a system how to behave when multiple raster images in a layer overlap each other, for example with satellite-image scenes.

ChiValue.Name: redSourcename
ChiValue.Notes: Colour Channels are identified by a system and data-dependent character identifier. Contrast enhancement may be applied to each channel in isolation.

ChiValue.Name: greenSourceName
ChiValue.Notes: Colour Channels are identified by a system and data-dependent character identifier. Contrast enhancement may be applied to each channel in isolation.

ChiValue.Name: blueSourcename
ChiValue.Notes: Colour Channels are identified by a system and data-dependent character identifier. Contrast enhancement may be applied to each channel in isolation.

ChiValue.Name: graySourcename
ChiValue.Notes: A single colour channel may be selected to display in grayscale. Colour Channels are identified by a system and data-dependent character identifier. Contrast enhancement may be applied to each channel in isolation.

ChiValue.Name: brighnessOnly
ChiValue.Notes: If the BrightnessOnly flag is 0 (false, default), the shading is applied to the layer being rendered as the current RasterSymbol. If BrightnessOnly is 1 (true), the shading is applied to the brightness of the colors in the rendering canvas generated so far by other layers, with the effect of relief-shading these other layers.

ChiValue.Name: reliefFactor
ChiValue.Notes: The ReliefFactor gives the amount of exaggeration to use for the height of the "hills". A value of around 55 (times) gives reasonable results for Earth-based DEMs. The default value is system-dependent.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlSelector
ChiNode.Notes: A diagram element that allows selection by a user, i.e. as "hyperNode" for navigating between diagrams, or as composite object representing multiple grouped objects.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlStroke
ChiNode.Notes: The element encapsulating the graphical symbolization parameters for linear geometries.

ChiValue.Name: opacity
ChiValue.Notes:
Specifies the level of translucency to use when rendering the stroke. The value is encoded as a floating-point value
between 0.0 and 1.0 with 0.0 representing completely transparent and 1.0 representing completely opaque, with a linear scale of translucency for intermediate values. The default value is 1.0

ChiValue.Name: width
ChiValue.Notes: The absolute width (thickness) of a stroke in pixels encoded as a float. The default is 1.0. Fractional numbers are allowed (with a system-dependent interpretation) but negative numbers are not.

ChiValue.Name: linejoin
ChiValue.Notes:
Enumerated values telling how line strings should be joined (between line segments). The values are represented as content strings.
The allowed values for line join are "mitre", "round", and "bevel". The default values are system-dependent.

ChiValue.Name: lineCap
ChiValue.Notes:
Enumerated values telling how line strings should be capped (at the two ends of the line string). The values are represented as content strings.
The allowed values for line cap are "butt", "round", and "square". The default values are system-dependent.

ChiValue.Name: lineStyle
ChiValue.Notes: The name of a defined line style. Usually will be an enumerated value and will be system-specific.

ChiValue.Name: dashArray
ChiValue.Notes: Encodes a dash pattern as a series of space separated floats. The first number gives the length in pixels of dash to draw, the second gives the amount of space to leave, and this pattern repeats. If an odd number of values is given, then the pattern is expanded by repeating it twice to give an even number of values. Decimal values have a system-dependent interpretation (usually depending on whether antialiasing is being used). The default is to draw an unbroken line.

ChiValue.Name: dashOffset
ChiValue.Notes: Specifies the distance as a float into the "stroke-dasharray" pattern at which to start drawing.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlSvgParameter
ChiNode.Notes: Refers to an SVG/CSS graphical-formatting parameter. The parameter is identified using the "name" attribute and the content of the element gives the SVG/CSS-coded value.

ChiValue.Name: attribute
ChiValue.Notes: The attribute of the GmlSvgParameter. E.g., for "Stroke", the following SvgParameters may be used: "stroke" (color), "stroke-opacity", "stroke-width", "stroke-linejoin", "stroke-linecap", "stroke-dasharray", and "stroke-dashoffset". Others are not officially supported.

ChiValue.Name: value
ChiValue.Notes: The SVG/CSS-coded value of the associated SvgAttribute.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlSymbol
ChiNode.Notes: Describes how a feature is to appear on a map or display. The symbol describes not just the shape that should appear but also such graphical properties as color and opacity.

ChiValue.Name: type
ChiValue.Notes: The Symbol type.

ChiValue.Name: level
ChiValue.Notes: The level (of the map) where the symbol exists or the zoom levels at which this diagram object is displayed. As a way of de-cluttering displays, for example, some symbols and annotations are only shown when zoomed in.

ChiValue.Name: version
ChiValue.Notes: The version of the Symbol.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlTextSymbol
ChiNode.Notes: Used for styling text labels, i.e., for rendering them according to various graphical parameters.

ChiValue.Name: label
ChiValue.Notes: Text-label content. If the value is not provided, then no text will be rendered.

ChiValue.Name: labelType
ChiValue.Notes: The type-classification of a label.

ChiValue.Name: minFontSize
ChiValue.Notes: The minimum font size allowed.

ChiValue.Name: property
ChiValue.Notes: Generic method for capturing all unspecified information pertaining to the TextSymbol.

ChiValue.Name: fieldID
ChiValue.Notes: The name of the field of the class being annotated. Most objects will include name, description, and aliasName. Many objects may contain other fields such as comment, status, etc.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlTopologyStyle
ChiNode.Notes: The style for one topology property. Similarly to the Geometry style, a feature can have multiple topology properties, thus multiple topology style descriptors can be specified within one feature style.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GmlValue
ChiNode.Notes: Used for direct representation of values.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ConnectDisconnectFunction
ChiNode.Notes: A function that will disconnect or reconnect the customer's load under defined conditions.

ChiValue.Name: isLocalAutoDiscOp
ChiValue.Notes: Applicable to a disconnection that can be operated locally; If set true, the operation happens automatically, otherwise it happens manually.

ChiValue.Name: isLocalAutoReconOp
ChiValue.Notes: If set true and if reconnection can be operated locally, then the operation happens automatically. Otherwise, it is manually.

ChiValue.Name: isRemoteAutoDiscOp
ChiValue.Notes: If set true and if disconnection can be operated remotely, then the operation happens automatically. If set false and if disconnection can be operated remotely, then the operation happens manually.

ChiValue.Name: isRemoteAutoReconOp
ChiValue.Notes: If set true and if reconnection can be operated remotely, then the operation happens automatically. If false and if reconnection can be operated remotely, then the operation happens manually.

ChiValue.Name: isDelayedDiscon
ChiValue.Notes: If set true, the switch may disconnect the service at the end of a specified time delay after the disconnect signal had been given. If set false, the switch may disconnect the service immediately after the disconnect signal had been given. This is typically the case for over current circuit-breakers which are classified as either instantaneous or slow acting.

ChiValue.Name: eventCount
ChiValue.Notes: An event is either connect or a disconnect action. A running cumulative count is kept of events for the lifetime of the function or until the value is cleared.

ChiValue.Name: isConnected
ChiValue.Notes: True if this function is in the connected state, otherwise it is in disconnected state.

ChiValue.Name: rcdInfo
ChiValue.Notes: Information on remote connect disconnect switch.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: LoadLimitFunction
ChiNode.Notes: A kind of LoadMgmtFunction that limits the customer load to a given value.

ChiValue.Name: isAutoReconOp
ChiValue.Notes: True if the switch will reconnect automatically, otherwise it will reconnect under manual control.

ChiValue.Name: disconnectTimeDelay
ChiValue.Notes: From the point when the maximumLoad threshold is crossed there may be a finite delay before the switch actually disconnects the load. Typically this is to buffer against transient load fluctuations.

ChiValue.Name: maximumLoad
ChiValue.Notes: The power level, to which the customer load is being limited when this function activates. When the maximum load is exceeded the switch will typically open to shed the complete customer load.

ChiValue.Name: reconnectTimeDelay
ChiValue.Notes: From the point when the load recovers from an overload condition and crosses the maximumLoad threshold going down, there may be a finite time delay before the switch actually reconnects the load. Typically this is to give overload conditions sufficient time to clear, thus preventing unnecessary load switching activity.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: LoadMgmtFunction
ChiNode.Notes: A collective function at an end device that manages the customer load.

ChiValue.Name: manualOverRide
ChiValue.Notes: True if the currently active schedule is being manually over-ridden to either shed load or to limit load.

ChiValue.Name: remoteOverRide
ChiValue.Notes: True if the currently active schedule is being remotely over-ridden to either shed load or to limit load.

ChiValue.Name: overRideTimeOut
ChiValue.Notes: After a command had been received to activate the mannualOverRide state or remoteOverRideState, the normal (halted) schedule will resume after this specified time duration had elapsed.

ChiValue.Name: loadStatus
ChiValue.Notes: The present state of the load being either shed (noLoad), limited (limitedLoad) or fully connected (fullLoad). This refers only to the portion of the customer load that is under control of the LoadMgmtFunction.

ChiValue.Name: isAutoOp
ChiValue.Notes: True if LoadMgmtFunction operates under automatic control, otherwise it operates under manual control.

ChiValue.Name: schedulingBasis
ChiValue.Notes: The basis of Load Management scheduling used here: Time Based, Tariff Based, Remote Control and Manual Control.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: LoadMgmtRecord
ChiNode.Notes: A log of actual measured load reductions as a result of load shed operations.

ChiValue.Name: loadReduction
ChiValue.Notes: The measured reduction of the total load power as a result of the load shed activation. Thus it is the difference in power before and after the load shed operation.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: LoadShedFunction
ChiNode.Notes: A kind of LoadMgmtFunction that sheds a part of the customer load.

ChiValue.Name: switchedLoad
ChiValue.Notes: The value of the load that is connected to the shedding switch. Typically this is a noted nominal value rather than a measured value.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: RemoteConnectDisconnectInfo
ChiNode.Notes: Details of remote connect disconnect function.

ChiValue.Name: isArmConnect
ChiValue.Notes: True if the RCD switch must be armed before a connect action can be initiated.

ChiValue.Name: isArmDisonnect
ChiValue.Notes: True if the RCD switch must be armed before a disconnect action can be initiated.

ChiValue.Name: armedTimeout
ChiValue.Notes: Setting of the timeout elapsed time.

ChiValue.Name: needsVoltageLimitCheck
ChiValue.Notes: True if voltage limit must be checked to prevent connect if voltage is over the limit.

ChiValue.Name: needsPowerLimitCheck
ChiValue.Notes: True if load limit must be checked to issue an immediate disconnect (after a connect) if load is over the limit.

ChiValue.Name: customerVoltageLimit
ChiValue.Notes: Voltage limit on customer side of RCD switch above which the connect should not be made.

ChiValue.Name: powerLimit
ChiValue.Notes: Load limit above which the connect should either not take place or should cause an immediate disconnect.

ChiValue.Name: usePushbutton
ChiValue.Notes: True if pushbutton must be used for connect.

ChiValue.Name: isEnergyLimiting
ChiValue.Notes: True if the energy usage is limited and the customer will be disconnected if they go over the limit.

ChiValue.Name: energyLimit
ChiValue.Notes: Limit of energy before disconnect.

ChiValue.Name: energyUsageWarning
ChiValue.Notes: Warning energy limit, used to trigger event code that energy usage is nearing limit.

ChiValue.Name: energyUsageStartDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Start date and time to accumulate energy for energy usage limiting.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AssetLocRole
ChiNode.Notes: Roles played between Assets and Locations.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: DocLocRole
ChiNode.Notes: Roles played between Documents and Locations. For example, as ErpAddress is a type of Location and WorkBilling is a type of Document, a role is the address for which to mail the invoice. As a TroubleTicket is a type of Document, one instance of Location may be the address for which the trouble is reported.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpPersonLocRole
ChiNode.Notes: Roles played between People and Locations. Some Locations are somewhat static, like the person's home address. Other may be dynamic, for example when the person is part of a crew driving around in truck.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Hazard
ChiNode.Notes: A hazard is any object or condition that is a danger for causing loss or perils to an asset and/or people. Examples of hazards are trees growing under overhead power lines, a park being located by a substation (i.e., children climb fence to recover a ball), a lake near an overhead distribution line (fishing pole/line contacting power lines), etc.

ChiValue.Name: category
ChiValue.Notes: Category by utility's corporate standards and practices.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: LandProperty
ChiNode.Notes: Information about a particular piece of (land) property such as its use. Ownership of the property may be determined through associations to Organisations and/or ErpPersons.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: LocationGrant
ChiNode.Notes: A grant provides a right, as defined by type, for a parcel of land. Note that the association to Location, Asset, Organisation, etc. for the Grant is inherited from Agreement, a type of Document.

ChiValue.Name: propertyData
ChiValue.Notes: Property related information that describes the Grant's land parcel. For example, it may be a deed book number, deed book page number, and parcel number.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: LocLocRole
ChiNode.Notes: The relationship between one Location and another Location. One "roleType" is "Directions," for which an additional attribute serves for providing a textual description for navigating from one location to another location.

ChiValue.Name: directionInfo
ChiValue.Notes: Detailed directional information.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: OrgLocRole
ChiNode.Notes: Roles played between Organisations and Locations, for example a service territory or school district. Note that roles dealing with use of a specific piece of property should be defined based on the relationship between OccupationsOfProperty and Location.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: OrgPropertyRole
ChiNode.Notes: Roles played between Organisations and a given piece of property. For example, the Organisation may be the owner, renter, occupier, taxiing authority, etc.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: PersonPropertyRole
ChiNode.Notes: The role of a person relative to a given piece of property. Examples of roles include: owner, renter, contractor, etc.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: PsrLocRole
ChiNode.Notes: Roles played between Power System Resources and Locations.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: RedLine
ChiNode.Notes: This class is used for handling the accompanying annotations, time stamp, author, etc. of designs, drawings and maps. A red line can be associated with any Location object.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: RightOfWay
ChiNode.Notes: A right-of-way (ROW) is for land where it is lawful to use for a public road, an electric power line, etc. Note that the association to Location, Asset, Organisation, etc. for the Grant is inherited from Agreement, a type of Document.

ChiValue.Name: propertyData
ChiValue.Notes: Property related information that describes the ROW's land parcel. For example, it may be a deed book number, deed book page number, and parcel number.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Route
ChiNode.Notes: Route that is followed, for example by service crews and meter readers.

ChiValue.Name: category
ChiValue.Notes: Category by utility's work management standards and practices.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Zone
ChiNode.Notes: Area divided off from other areas. It may be part of the electrical network, a land area where special restrictions apply, weather areas, etc. For weather, it is an area where a set of relatively homogenous weather measurements apply.

ChiValue.Name: kind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of this zone.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ComPort
ChiNode.Notes: Port information used for communication connectivity purposes. The "port" names the physical association to another device from the perspective of the parent asset. For example, a communications module may need to list the meters which it can talk to as meter serial number "123" is on "port 0", S/N "456" is on port "1", etc. A meter or load control device may need to know that a hot-water heater load is on "port 0", and an air-conditioner on "port 1".

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GasMeteringFunction
ChiNode.Notes: Functionality performed by a gas meter. It's entirely possible that the metering system would carry information to/from gas meters even though it was built primarily to carry the higher-value electric meter data.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: MeteringFunctionConfiguration
ChiNode.Notes: The configuration of data for a given meter function.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: WaterMeteringFunction
ChiNode.Notes: Functionality performed by a water meter. It's entirely possible that the metering system would carry information to/from water meters even though it was built primarily to carry the higher-value electric meter data.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CallBack
ChiNode.Notes: Information about a planned CallBack or a CallBack that has occurred, from the utility to a customer regarding the status and plans about resolving trouble, performing work, etc.

ChiValue.Name: contactDetail
ChiValue.Notes: Additional contact details that are not provided for ErpPerson with ErpTelephoneNumber.

ChiValue.Name: dateTime
ChiValue.Notes: (if callback already occured) Date and time when this call back occurred.

ChiValue.Name: advice
ChiValue.Notes: Advice already given to the customer during this call back.

ChiValue.Name: problemInfo
ChiValue.Notes: Descriptiion of the problem reported during this call back.

ChiValue.Name: comment
ChiValue.Notes: Comments by customer during this call back.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ChangeSet
ChiNode.Notes: The updates required in a transaction for an existing data set are grouped into a single ChangeSet. In data sets (e.g., NetworkDataSet), each major step in the ChangeSet is described through a separate ChangeItem associated with the data set. Within each data set, each inidividual object change is described with a seperate ChangeItem associated with the object.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Circuit
ChiNode.Notes: Static collection of conducting equipment originating at a main distribution center and supplying one or more secondary distribution centers, one or more branch-circuit distribution centers, or any combination of these two types of equipment. It is the source to the next normally open point.

ChiValue.Name: ratedVoltage
ChiValue.Notes: Rated voltage of the circuit.

ChiValue.Name: connectionKind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of this circuit.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CircuitSection
ChiNode.Notes: Section of circuit located between two sectionalizing devices. It may contain other circuit sections, for example, a lateral tapped off a primary.

ChiValue.Name: connectionKind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of this circuit section.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ComplianceEvent
ChiNode.Notes:
Compliance events are used for reporting regulatory or contract compliance issues and/or variances. These might be created as a consequence of local business processes and associated rules. It is anticipated that this class will be customised extensively to meet local implementation needs.
Use inherited 'category' to indicate that, for example, expected performance will not be met or reported as mandated.

ChiValue.Name: complianceType
ChiValue.Notes: Type of compliance event indicating, for example, types of regulatory and/or contractual compliance events where expected performance will not be met or reported as mandated.

ChiValue.Name: deadline
ChiValue.Notes: The deadline for compliance.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ErpPersonScheduleStepRole
ChiNode.Notes: Roles played between Persons and Schedule Steps.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: IncidentCode
ChiNode.Notes: Classification of incident types. Multiple incident codes may apply to a given incident. The primary overall incident cause is recorded in 'IncidentRecord.category', and the main code in 'name'.

ChiValue.Name: subCode
ChiValue.Notes: Additional level of classification detail (as extension to the main code found in 'name').

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: IncidentRecord
ChiNode.Notes: Document describing the incident reported in a TroubleTicket. If the incident has to do with an outage, this will be associated with an OutageRecord. Primary cause of the incident is captured in 'category'.

ChiValue.Name: endDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time incident was resolved for all customers impacted by this incident.

ChiValue.Name: startDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time first customer was impacted by the incident.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: LandBase
ChiNode.Notes: Land base data.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: NetworkDataSet
ChiNode.Notes: Categorized as a type of document, model of a portion of the electrical network that includes a list of the equipment, along with relevant connectivity, electrical characteristics, geographical location, and various parameters associated with the equipment.

ChiValue.Name: category
ChiValue.Notes: Category of network data set.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: OperationalRestriction
ChiNode.Notes:
A document that can be associated with a device to describe any sort of restrictions compared with the original manufacturer's specification e.g. temporary maximum loadings, maximum switching current, do not operate if bus couplers are open etc etc.
In the UK, for example, if a breaker or switch ever mal-operates, this is reported centrally and utilities use their asset systems to identify all the installed devices of the same manufacturer's type. They then apply operational restrictions in the operational systems to warn operators of potential problems. After appropriate inspection and maintenance, the operational restrictions may be removed.

ChiValue.Name: endDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time restriction is lifted.

ChiValue.Name: reason
ChiValue.Notes: Reason for applying restriction.

ChiValue.Name: startDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time restriction is applied.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: OrgPsrRole
ChiNode.Notes: Roles played between Organisations and Power System Resources.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: OutageCode
ChiNode.Notes:
Classification of outage types. Multiple outage codes may apply to a given outage or outage step.The primary overall outage type is recorded in OutageRecord.outageType. There may be more than one classification per outage step and/or per outage record.
Example codes/subcodes include: weather/ice, weather/lightning, wildlife/squirrel, wildlife/bird, burned/overload, burned/weather, wire down/accident, wire down/tree, wire down/vandalism, etc.
The typical "outage code" is in the inherited "name" attribute. The code is described in the inherited "description" attribute.

ChiValue.Name: subCode
ChiValue.Notes: The main code is stored in the inherited .name. This sub-code provides an additional level of classification detail.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: OutageNotification
ChiNode.Notes: A document containing information to be sent to customers notifying that an outage will take place. This is used to generate mailing lists for customers.

ChiValue.Name: duration
ChiValue.Notes: Likely duration of the interruption(s).

ChiValue.Name: expectedInterruptionCount
ChiValue.Notes: Number of possible interruptions that the customer may expect for this event.

ChiValue.Name: reason
ChiValue.Notes: Details of the outage "reason".

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: OutageRecord
ChiNode.Notes:
A document describing details of an outage in part of the electrical network, typically produced by a SCADA system following a breaker trip, or within a Trouble Call System by grouping customer calls. This has an associated OutageStep for each supply point. Primary cause of the outage is captured in 'category'.
In some countries all outage restoration is performed using a SwitchingSchedule which complements the OutageRecord and records the ErpPersons (crew) and any planned Work. In other systems, it may be acceptable to manage outages including new WorkTasks without switching schedules.
Note: The relationship between OutageRecord and ErpPerson and Crew is inherited as each is a type of Document.

ChiValue.Name: endDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time restoration was completed for all customers impacted by this outage.

ChiValue.Name: isPlanned
ChiValue.Notes: True if planned, false otherwise (for example due to a breaker trip).

ChiValue.Name: actionTaken
ChiValue.Notes: Overall action taken to resolve outage (details are in 'WorkTasks').

ChiValue.Name: damageCode
ChiValue.Notes: The damage code relative to the associated PowerSystemResource(s) and/or Asset(s). Examples include broken, burnout, failure, flashed (burned), manually operated, wire down, no damage - rolling blackout, none.

ChiValue.Name: mode
ChiValue.Notes: Value of ErpOrganisation.mode at the time of OutageRecord.startDateTime.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: OutageReport
ChiNode.Notes: Document with statistics of an outage.

ChiValue.Name: customerCount
ChiValue.Notes: Total number of outaged customers.

ChiValue.Name: outageDuration
ChiValue.Notes: Total outage duration.

ChiValue.Name: averageCml
ChiValue.Notes: Average Customer Minutes Lost (CML) for this outage.

ChiValue.Name: totalCml
ChiValue.Notes: Total Customer Minutes Lost (CML).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: OutageStep
ChiNode.Notes: Holds an outage start and end time for each supply point of an outage record. The supply point for a given step is the associated PowerSystemResource instance.

ChiValue.Name: totalCustomerCount
ChiValue.Notes: Number of customers connected to the PowerSystemResource.

ChiValue.Name: specialCustomerCount
ChiValue.Notes: Number of customers with high reliability required.

ChiValue.Name: criticalCustomerCount
ChiValue.Notes: Number of customers with critical needs, e.g., with a dialysis machine.

ChiValue.Name: callerCount
ChiValue.Notes: Number of customers phoning in.

ChiValue.Name: fatality
ChiValue.Notes: True if fatalities reported by caller or engineer.

ChiValue.Name: injury
ChiValue.Notes: True if injuries reported by caller or engineer.

ChiValue.Name: noPowerInterval
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time interval between loss and restoration of power.

ChiValue.Name: shockReported
ChiValue.Notes: True if shocks reported by caller or engineer.

ChiValue.Name: damage
ChiValue.Notes: True if damage reported by caller or engineer.

ChiValue.Name: estimatedRestoreDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Estimated time of restoration.

ChiValue.Name: averageCml
ChiValue.Notes: Average Customer Minutes Lost (CML) for this supply point for this outage.

ChiValue.Name: totalCml
ChiValue.Notes: Total Customer Minutes Lost (CML) for this supply point for this outage.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: OutageStepPsrRole
ChiNode.Notes: Roles played between Power System Resources and Outage Steps. Examples roles include: normal supply, actual supply, interrupting device, restoration device.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: PlannedOutage
ChiNode.Notes: Planned outage involves network operations which will affect the supply of power to customers. Note that the list of Power System Resources for the PlannedOutage may be the same or a superset of the ones per OutageStep.

ChiValue.Name: kind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of outage.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: SafetyDocument
ChiNode.Notes:
Document used during the course of work on the electrical system for safety purposes.
Note: ClearanceTag is a special case of a Safety Document.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: SwitchingSchedule
ChiNode.Notes:
Document describing a sequence of steps to perform an item of work, for example to isolate some plant with regard to safety, equipment ratings, and standards of customer service.
Note 1: SwitchingSchedule is intended to describe the full operational details for switching for real time operation which includes other operations such as grounding, applying safety documents etc.
Note 2: The association to ErpPerson suits the UK practice of quoting specific names (e.g the crew foreman). The association to Crew is for US practice.

ChiValue.Name: endDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Completion date and time of switching.

ChiValue.Name: reason
ChiValue.Notes: Reason for switching.

ChiValue.Name: startDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Start date and time of switching.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: SwitchingStep
ChiNode.Notes:
A single step within a SwitchingSchedule. Could be a switching operation (applying a network alteration), or issuing a safety document.
Note: Inherited attribute IdentifiedObject.name is used to hold the sequence number.

ChiValue.Name: instructedDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: The time and date that the Required Control Action was issued.

ChiValue.Name: completedDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: The time and date that the Required Control Action was completed.

ChiValue.Name: requiredControlAction
ChiValue.Notes: Control actions required to perform this step.

ChiValue.Name: text
ChiValue.Notes: Information regarding this switching schedule step.

ChiValue.Name: desiredEndState
ChiValue.Notes: Desired end state for the associated PowerSystemResource as a result of this schedule step.

ChiValue.Name: statusKind
ChiValue.Notes: Status of this SwitchingStep.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TroubleTicket
ChiNode.Notes:
A document used to report electrical trouble. The trouble may either be an outage or non-outage problem, such as power quality. It must always be associated with an Incident Record.
Note that a separate Activity Record is created for each call associated with an instance of Trouble Ticket. The time of a call is stored in ActivityRecord.createdOn and comments are recorded in ActivityRecord.remarks.

ChiValue.Name: priority
ChiValue.Notes: Priority of trouble call.

ChiValue.Name: firstCallDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time trouble call first received. The date and time of subsequent calls by the same customer for the same trouble are recorded in associated Activity Records.

ChiValue.Name: reportingKind
ChiValue.Notes: Means the customer used to report trouble (default is 'call').

ChiValue.Name: advice
ChiValue.Notes: Advice already given to the customer at time when trouble was first reported.

ChiValue.Name: startDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time at which this source of trouble started.

ChiValue.Name: restorationTime
ChiValue.Notes: Time of restoration of resolution of trouble.

ChiValue.Name: estimatedRestoreDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Estimated restoration date and time last provided to the customer.

ChiValue.Name: hazardCode
ChiValue.Notes: Code for a reported hazard condition.

ChiValue.Name: informBeforeRestored
ChiValue.Notes: True if person reporting trouble requested a call back when sigificant information became available about cause of the outage and the estimated restoration time. The person and their contact information are maintained in the assoicated Customer information. Call back results are recorded in assoicated 'ActivityRecord.Status.remarks'.

ChiValue.Name: informAfterRestored
ChiValue.Notes: True if person reporting trouble requested a call back to confirm power has been restored. The person and their contact information is maintained in the assoicated Customer informaiton. Call back results are recorded in assoicated 'ActivityRecord.Status.remarks'.

ChiValue.Name: callBack
ChiValue.Notes: True if requested to customer when someone is about to arrive at their premises.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Bank
ChiNode.Notes: Organisation that is a commercial bank, agency, or other institution that offers a similar service.

ChiValue.Name: branchCode
ChiValue.Notes: Codified reference to the particular branch of the bank where BankAccount is held.

ChiValue.Name: iban
ChiValue.Notes: International bank account number defined in ISO 13616; for countries where IBAN is not in operation, the existing BIC or SWIFT codes may be used instead (see ISO 9362).

ChiValue.Name: bic
ChiValue.Notes: Bank identifier code as defined in ISO 9362; for use in countries wher IBAN is not yet in operation.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: BankStatement
ChiNode.Notes: A type of Document that records bank deposits made by Vendor of revenue collected at PointOfSale.

ChiValue.Name: depositAmount
ChiValue.Notes: The amount that is deposited into the bank via BankAccount.

ChiValue.Name: depositDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: The date and time the deposit is made.

ChiValue.Name: merchantCreditAmount
ChiValue.Notes: The amount on this statement that is to be credited to MerchantAccount.

ChiValue.Name: posted
ChiValue.Notes: True if mechantCreditAmount has been cerdited to MerchantAccount; typically happens when bank statement details are captured into payment system.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ChargeRegister
ChiNode.Notes: Accumulated charges transacted per ChargeKind for a given function. There could be several of these registers, one for each ChargeKind; depending on the application.

ChiValue.Name: chargeAmount
ChiValue.Notes: Charge amount in favour of the supplier. The units are either in currency units or service units, depending on the value of 'AccountingUnit.accountingMode'.

ChiValue.Name: chargeKind
ChiValue.Notes:
Several different types of charges are typically implemented in the case of a prepayment meter.
For example: a charge according to a tariff for consumption and possibly a demand component, or a charge for a debt that is loaded in the meter to be recovered on a time basis, or a standing charge to be levied at the end of each billing period, or a tax charge loaded in the meter to be recovered on a consumption basis or a time basis.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CreditRegister
ChiNode.Notes: Accumulated credits transacted per CreditKind for a given function. There could be several of these registers, one for each CreditKind; depending on the application.

ChiValue.Name: creditAmount
ChiValue.Notes: Credit amount in favour of the customer. The units are either in currency units or service units, depending on the value of 'AccountingUnit.accountingMode'.

ChiValue.Name: creditKind
ChiValue.Notes:
Several different types of credit are typically implemented in the case of a prepayment meter.
For example: credit transferred by means of a token carrier, or credit advanced automatically inside the meter under certain conditions, or credit held in reserved to be released under emergency conditions, or credit granted by local authority as a basic life support mechanism and may be dispensed automatically by the meter under certain conditions or credit available under severe climate conditions such as during winter over a weekend.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: SDPAccountingFunction
ChiNode.Notes: Service delivery point accounting function, particularly for payment meter.

ChiValue.Name: availableCredit
ChiValue.Notes:
The value is the balance of the sum of credits minus the sum of charges from the CreditRegisters and the ChargeRegisters. The sum might be complex function.
The units are either in currency units or service units, depending on the value of accountingMode.

ChiValue.Name: lowCreditWarningLevel
ChiValue.Notes:
The value is a predefined set point for the level of the availableCredit to reach when a warning will be indicated to the customer. It serves to warn the customer that it is time to purchase more credit in the case of a prepayment meter implementation.
The units are either in currency units or service units, depending on the value of accountingMode.

ChiValue.Name: creditExpiryLevel
ChiValue.Notes:
The value is a predefined set point for the level of the availableCredit to reach when the service will be interrupted. In the case of a prepayment meter the interruption is typically implemented by means of an electro-mechanical switch and the value is typically set = 0.
The units are either in currency units or service units, depending on the value of accountingMode.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Token
ChiNode.Notes: The token that is transferred to the payment meter.

ChiValue.Name: code
ChiValue.Notes: Coded representation of the token that is transferred to the payment meter.

ChiValue.Name: comment
ChiValue.Notes: Free-format note relevant to this token.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TSPAgreement
ChiNode.Notes: A contractual agreement between a supplier (utility) and a transaction service provider (a type of organisation) that governs the terms and conditions, under which authorisation the transaction service provider may process transactions on behalf of the supplier.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AssetFunctionTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic Asset Function that may be used for various purposes such as work planning.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: BreakerTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic breaker asset that may be used for design purposes.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: BusbarTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic busbar that may be used for design purposes. It is typically associated with PoserSystemResource BusbarSection.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: BushingTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic bushing that may be used for various purposes such as work planning.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CabinetTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic cabinet that may be used for various purposes such as work planning.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CableTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic cable that may be used for various purposes such as work planning. It is a specialisation of LinearConductor that includes attributes specific to underground cables.

ChiValue.Name: shieldThickness
ChiValue.Notes: Thickness of the shielding

ChiValue.Name: outsideDiameter
ChiValue.Notes: Outside diameter over the shield (inches) for a non concentric neutral cable.

ChiValue.Name: conductorSpacing
ChiValue.Notes: Phase conductor spacing for a three conductor cable if a distribution model is given.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ComEquipmentTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a piece of Communication Equipment (e.g., gateway, router, network hub, etc.) that may be used for design purposes.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ComFunctionTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic communication function that may be used for various purposes such as work planning.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CompositeSwitchTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic composite switch asset that may be used for design purposes. A composite wwitch is an amalgamation of multiple Switches.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Connection
ChiNode.Notes: A structure can have multiple connection points for electrical connections (e.g. line) each with multiple mounting points, one for each phase. e.g. a Tower may have three Connections, two with three mounting points, one for each phase and a third with a single mounting point for the neutral line. A pole, on the other hand, may have a single Connection with one, two or three mounting points depending on whether it is carrying 1,2 or 3 phases.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CurrentTransformerTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic Current Transformer (CT) that may be used for various purposes such as work planning.

ChiValue.Name: accuracyClass
ChiValue.Notes: CT accuracy classification

ChiValue.Name: coreCount
ChiValue.Notes: Number of cores.

ChiValue.Name: usage
ChiValue.Notes: eg. metering, protection, etc

ChiValue.Name: coreBurden
ChiValue.Notes: Power burden of the CT core

ChiValue.Name: kneePointVoltage
ChiValue.Notes: Maximum voltage across the secondary terminals where the CT still displays linear characteristicts.

ChiValue.Name: kneePointCurrent
ChiValue.Notes: Maximum primary current where the CT still displays linear characteristicts.

ChiValue.Name: nominalRatio
ChiValue.Notes: Nominal ratio between the primary and secondary current; i.e. 100:5

ChiValue.Name: maxRatio
ChiValue.Notes: Maximum ratio between the primary and secondary current.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: DuctBankTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: A DuctBank contains multiple Ducts. The DuctBank itself should have no connections, since these are defined by the individual ducts within it. However, it will have a ConstructionType and the material it is constructed from.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: DuctTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: A Duct contains underground cables and is contained within a duct bank. The xCoord and yCoord attributes define its positioning within the DuctBank.

ChiValue.Name: xCoord
ChiValue.Notes: X position of the duct within the duct bank.

ChiValue.Name: yCoord
ChiValue.Notes: Y position of the duct within the duct bank.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ElecAMElecPropRole
ChiNode.Notes: ElectricalAssetModel - ElectrialProperties Role. Used to define what the properties refers to in the AssetModel. e.g. for a Transformer, it will have an association to an instance of ElectricalProperties for each Winding, with the roleType defining whether it is the primary, secondary, tertiary, quartiary winding.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ElecTAElecPropRole
ChiNode.Notes: ElectricalTypeAsset - ElectrialProperties Role. Used to define what the properties refers to in the TypeAsset. e.g. for a Transformer, it will have an association to an instance of ElectricalProperties for each Winding, with the roleType defining whether it is the primary, secondary, tertiary, quartiary winding.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ElectricalTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Generic TypeAsset for all types of component in the network that have electrical characteristics.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: EndDeviceTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for generic End Device that may be used for various purposes such as work planning.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: FACTSDeviceTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for generic Flexible alternating current transmission systems (FACTS) devices that may be used for various purposes such as work planning.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: FaultIndicatorTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic fault indicator that may be used for design purposes.

ChiValue.Name: resetKind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of reset mechanisim of this fault indicator.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GeneratorTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for generic generation equipment that may be used for various purposes such as work planning. It defines both the Real and Reactive power properties (modelled at the PSR level as a GeneratingUnit + SynchronousMachine)

ChiValue.Name: maxQ
ChiValue.Notes: Maximum reactive power limit.

ChiValue.Name: maxP
ChiValue.Notes: Maximum real power limit.

ChiValue.Name: minQ
ChiValue.Notes: Minimum reactive power generated.

ChiValue.Name: minP
ChiValue.Notes: Minimum real power generated.

ChiValue.Name: rDirectSubtrans
ChiValue.Notes: Direct-axis subtransient resistance

ChiValue.Name: rDirectSync
ChiValue.Notes: Direct-axis synchronous resistance

ChiValue.Name: rDirectTrans
ChiValue.Notes: Direct-axis Transient resistance

ChiValue.Name: rQuadSubtrans
ChiValue.Notes: Quadrature-axis subtransient resistance

ChiValue.Name: rQuadSync
ChiValue.Notes: Quadrature-axis synchronous resistance

ChiValue.Name: rQuadTrans
ChiValue.Notes: Quadrature-axis Transient resistance

ChiValue.Name: xDirectSubtrans
ChiValue.Notes: Direct-axis subtransient reactance

ChiValue.Name: xDirectSync
ChiValue.Notes: Direct-axis synchronous reactance

ChiValue.Name: xDirectTrans
ChiValue.Notes: Direct-axis Transient reactance

ChiValue.Name: xQuadSubtrans
ChiValue.Notes: Quadrature-axis subtransient reactance

ChiValue.Name: xQuadSync
ChiValue.Notes: Quadrature-axis synchronous reactance

ChiValue.Name: xQuadTrans
ChiValue.Notes: Quadrature-axis transient reactance.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: LinearConductorTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic linear conductor that may be used for various purposes such as work planning. ElectricalProperties are defined as being per unit length (which is defined by 'unitLength').

ChiValue.Name: insulated
ChiValue.Notes: True if conductor is insultated.

ChiValue.Name: radius
ChiValue.Notes: Radius of the conductor

ChiValue.Name: gmr
ChiValue.Notes: Geometric mean radius (GMR): If the conductor were replaced by a thin walled tube of radius with this value, then its reactance would be identical to that of the actual conductor.

ChiValue.Name: size
ChiValue.Notes: Commonly referred to size for this type of conductor.

ChiValue.Name: unitLength
ChiValue.Notes: Length of each unit of the LinearConductor which has characteristics defined by the associated ElectricalProperties.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: MeterTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic meter that may be used for design purposes. Rather than being associated with CustomerMeter, it is associated with EnergyConsumer as it may be used for many applications, such as tie line metering, in addition to customer metering.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: MountingPoint
ChiNode.Notes: Point on a structure that a connection may have a conductor connected to. Defined with an x and y coordinate plus a phase. A connection may have multiple mounting points, one for each phase.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: OverheadConductorTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic Overhead Conductor that may be used for various purposes such as work planning. It is a specialisation of LinearConductor that includes attributes specific to overhead lines.

ChiValue.Name: conductorCount
ChiValue.Notes: Number of conductor strands for a particular overhead conductor phase. Separate phases and their spacings are modelled by the MountingPoint positions for the structure the Overhead Conductor is supported by (e.g. pole, tower)

ChiValue.Name: conductorSpacing
ChiValue.Notes: Spacing between the individual conductor strands for a single overhead conductor phase.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: PoleTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic pole that may be used for various purposes such as work planning. A pole typically has a single Connection with 1,2 or 3 mounting points.

ChiValue.Name: diameter
ChiValue.Notes: Diameter of the pole.

ChiValue.Name: length
ChiValue.Notes: Length of the pole (inclusive of any section of the pole that may be underground post-installation).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: PotentialTransformerTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic Potential Transformer (PT) that may be used for various purposes such as work planning.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ProtectionEquipmentTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for generic protection equiment that may be used for design purposes.

ChiValue.Name: defaultGroundTrip
ChiValue.Notes: Default ground trip setting for this type of relay, if applicable.

ChiValue.Name: defaultPhaseTrip
ChiValue.Notes: Default phase trip setting for this type of relay, if applicable.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: RecloserTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic recloser asset that may be used for design purposes.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ResistorTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic resistor that may be used for design purposes.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: SeriesCompensatorTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic series compensator that may be used for design purposes.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ShuntCompensatorTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic shunt compensator that may be used for design purposes.

ChiValue.Name: maxPowerLoss
ChiValue.Notes: Maximum allowed Apparent Power loss

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: StreetlightTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic streetlight that may be used for various purposes such as work planning. Use 'category' for utility specific categorisation, such as luminar, grid light, lantern, open bottom, flood, etc.

ChiValue.Name: lightRating
ChiValue.Notes: Nominal (as designed) power rating of light.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: StructureTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: A Type of Structural Asset with properties common to a large number of asset models.

ChiValue.Name: ratedVoltage
ChiValue.Notes: Maximum rated voltage of the equipment that can be mounted on/contained within the structure.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: SubstationTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a type of substation that may be used for design purposes.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: SurgeProtectorTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic surge arrestor that may be used for design purposes.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: SVCTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic Static Var Compensator (SVC) that may be used for various purposes such as work planning.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: SwitchTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic switch asset that may be used for design purposes.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TapChangerTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for generic tap changers that may be used for various purposes such as work planning.

ChiValue.Name: highStep
ChiValue.Notes: Highest possible tap step position, advance from neutral

ChiValue.Name: lowStep
ChiValue.Notes: Lowest possible tap step position, retard from neutral

ChiValue.Name: neutralStep
ChiValue.Notes: The neutral tap step position for this type of winding.

ChiValue.Name: initialDelay
ChiValue.Notes: Maximum allowed delay for initial tap changer operation (first step change)

ChiValue.Name: subsequentDelay
ChiValue.Notes: Maximum allowed delay for isubsequent tap changer operations

ChiValue.Name: stepVoltageIncrement
ChiValue.Notes: Tap step increment, in per cent of nominal voltage, per step position.

ChiValue.Name: stepPhaseIncrement
ChiValue.Notes: Phase shift, in degrees, per step position

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ToolTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for a generic tool that may be used for various purposes such as work planning.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TowerTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes:
Documentation for a generic tower that may be used for various purposes such as work planning.
A transmission tower carrying two 3-phase circuits will have 2 instances of Connection, each of which will have 3 MountingPoint instances, one for each phase all with coordinates relative to a common origin on the tower. (It may also have a 3rd Connection with a single MountingPoint for the Neutral line).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TransformerTypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation for generic transformers that may be used for various purposes such as work planning.
