The operating voltages can be found via the ElectricalProperties class. e.g. a two winding transformer will have two instances of ElectricalProperties and the primary/secondaryWinding can be found from the ratedKV attributes of each and the ElecTAElecPropRole used to define which is the primaryWinding and which is the secondaryWinding.

ChiValue.Name: windingCount
ChiValue.Notes: Number of windings.

ChiValue.Name: coreLoss
ChiValue.Notes: Maximum loss of power in the transformer core.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TypeAsset
ChiNode.Notes:
Whereas an AssetModel is a particular model and version of a vendor's product, a TypeAsset is documentation for a generic asset or material item that may be used for design purposes.
Any number of AssetModels may be used to perform this generic function. The primary role of the TypeAsset is typically defined by the PowereSystemResource it is associated with.

ChiValue.Name: estimatedUnitCost
ChiValue.Notes: Estimated unit cost (or cost per unit length) of the this type of asset. It does not include labor to install/construct or configure it.

ChiValue.Name: quantity
ChiValue.Notes: The value, unit of measure, and multiplier for the quantity.

ChiValue.Name: stockItem
ChiValue.Notes: True if item is a stock item (default).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TypeAssetCatalogue
ChiNode.Notes: Catalogue of generic types of assets (TypeAsset) that may be used for design purposes. It is not associated with a particular manufacturer.

ChiNode.creator: admin

A design for consideration by customers, potential customers, or internal work.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TypeMaterial
ChiNode.Notes:
Documentation for a generic material item that may be used for design, work and other purposes. Any number of MaterialItems manufactured by various vendors may be used to perform this TypeMaterial.
Note that class analagous to "AssetModel" is not used for material items. This is because in some cases, for example, a utility sets up a Master material record for a 3 inch long half inch diameter steel bolt and they do not necessarily care what specific supplier is providing the material item. As different vendors are used to supply the part, the Stock Code of the material item can stay the same. In other cases, each time the vendor changes, a new stock code is set up so they can track material used by vendor. Therefore a Material Item "Model" is not typically needed.

ChiValue.Name: estUnitCost
ChiValue.Notes: The estimated unit cost of this type of material, either for a unit cost or cost per unit length. Cost is for material or asset only and does not include labor to install/construct or configure it.

ChiValue.Name: quantity
ChiValue.Notes: The value, unit of measure, and multiplier for the quantity.

ChiValue.Name: costType
ChiValue.Notes: The category of cost to which this Material Item belongs.

ChiValue.Name: stockItem
ChiValue.Notes: True if item is a stock item (default).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Usage
ChiNode.Notes: The way material and assets are used to perform a certain type of work task. The way is described in text in the inheritied description attribute.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: WorkCostDetail
ChiNode.Notes: A collection of all of the individual cost items collected from multiple sources.

ChiValue.Name: amount
ChiValue.Notes: Amount in designated currency for work, either a total or an individual element. As defined in the attribute "type," multiple instances are applicable to each work for: planned cost, actual cost, authorized cost, budgeted cost, forecasted cost, other.

ChiValue.Name: debitFlag
ChiValue.Notes: True if "amount" attribute is a debit, false if it is a credit.

ChiValue.Name: transactionDate
ChiValue.Notes: Date that amount is posted to the work.

ChiValue.Name: typeWorkCost
ChiValue.Notes: The type of cost.

ChiNode.Name: WorkCostSummary

ChiNode.Name: WorkFlowStep

ChiNode.Name: WorkLocation

ChiValue.Name: nearestIntersection

ChiValue.Name: subdivision
ChiValue.Notes: Name, identifier, or description of the subdivision, if applicable, in which work is to occur.

ChiValue.Name: lot
ChiValue.Notes: Name, identifier, or description of the lot, if applicable, in which work is to occur.

ChiValue.Name: block
ChiValue.Notes: Name, identifier, or description of the block, if applicable, in which work is to occur.

ChiNode.Name: WorkStatusEntry

ChiValue.Name: percentComplete

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: WorkTask
ChiNode.Notes: A set of tasks is required to implement a design.

ChiValue.Name: priority
ChiValue.Notes: The priority of this work task.

ChiValue.Name: schedOverride
ChiValue.Notes: If specified, override schedule and perform this task in accordance with instructions specified here.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AssetElement
ChiNode.Notes: this is am atomic asset that cannot contain other assets. special class introduced by the eenergy IBM project.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ComFunction
ChiNode.Notes: Communication function of communication equipment or a device such as a meter.

ChiValue.Name: amrAddress
ChiValue.Notes: Communication ID number (e.g. serial number, IP address, telephone number, etc.) of the AMR module which serves this meter.

ChiValue.Name: amrRouter
ChiValue.Notes:
Communication ID number (e.g. port number, serial number, data collector ID, etc.) of the parent device associated to this AMR module.
Note: The thought here is that if someone swaps out a meter, they may inadvertently disrupt the AMR system. Some technologies route readings from nearby meters through a common collection point on an electricity meter. Removal of such a meter disrupts AMR for numerous nearby meters.

ChiValue.Name: twoWay
ChiValue.Notes: True when the AMR module can both send and receive messages. Default is false (i.e., module can only send).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: DemandResponseProgram
ChiNode.Notes: Demand response program.

ChiValue.Name: type
ChiValue.Notes: Type of demand response program; examples are CPP (critical-peak pricing), RTP (real-time pricing), DLC (direct load control), DBP (demand bidding program), BIP (base interruptible program). Note that possible types change a lot and it would be impossible to enumerate them all.

ChiValue.Name: validityInterval
ChiValue.Notes: Interval within which the program is valid.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: DeviceFunction
ChiNode.Notes: Function performed by a device such as a meter, communication equipment, controllers, etc..

ChiValue.Name: disabled
ChiValue.Notes: True if the device function is disabled (deactivated). Default is false (i.e., function is enabled).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ElectricMeteringFunction
ChiNode.Notes: Functionality performed by an electric meter.

ChiValue.Name: kWhMultiplier
ChiValue.Notes: Meter kWh multiplier, used as a multiplier for a meter register reading to determine the actual amount of usage for which to bill a customer.

ChiValue.Name: kWMultiplier
ChiValue.Notes: Meter kW (pulse) multiplier, used as a multiplier for a meter register reading to determine the actual amount of usage for which to bill a customer.

ChiValue.Name: transformerRatiosApplied
ChiValue.Notes: True if these ratios have been already applied to the associated quantities.

ChiValue.Name: transformerCTRatio
ChiValue.Notes: Current transformer ratio used to convert associated quantities to real measurements.

ChiValue.Name: transformerVTRatio
ChiValue.Notes: Voltage transformer ratio used to convert associated quantities to real measurements.

ChiValue.Name: voltageRating
ChiValue.Notes: The service voltage at which the meter is designed to operate. Typical voltage ratings in North America are 120, 240, 277 or 480V.

ChiValue.Name: currentRating
ChiValue.Notes: The current class of the meter. Typical current classes in North America are 10, 20, 100, 200, or 320 A.

ChiValue.Name: billingMultiplierApplied
ChiValue.Notes: True if the billingMultiplier ratio has already been applied to the associated quantities.

ChiValue.Name: billingMultiplier
ChiValue.Notes: Customer billing value = meter multiplier * transformer ratios * reading value. The multiplier identifies the scaling value to apply to the reported value after delivery of the tagged item.

ChiValue.Name: demandMultiplierApplied
ChiValue.Notes: True if the demandMultiplier ratio has already been applied to the associated quantities.

ChiValue.Name: demandMultiplier
ChiValue.Notes: An additional multiplier that may be used for normalization of the demand value to an hourly value. For example, if the demand interval were set to 15 minutes, the demand multiplier would be 4. If the meter design is such that the demand value reported and displayed is compensated for by the meter itself and no additional scaling is required outside of the meter, the value of the demand multiplier should be "1".

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: EndDeviceAsset
ChiNode.Notes:
AssetContainer that performs one or more end device functions. One type of EndDeviceAsset is a MeterAsset which can perform metering, load management, connect/disconnect, accounting functions, etc. Some EndDeviceAssets, such as ones monitoring and controlling air conditioner, refrigerator, pool pumps may be connected to a MeterAsset. All EndDeviceAssets may have communication capability defined by the associated ComFunction(s). An EndDeviceAsset may be owned by a consumer, a service provider, utility or otherwise.
There may be a related end device function that identifies a sensor or control point within a metering applicaiton or communications systems (e.g., water, gas, electricity).
Some devices may use an optical port that conforms to the ANSI C12.18 standard for communications.

ChiValue.Name: disconnect
ChiValue.Notes: True when this EndDeviceAsset is capable of supporting remote whole-house disconnect capability. To determine whether this functionality is installed and enabled, check the 'disabled' attribute of the associated device function contained by this EndDeviceAsset.

ChiValue.Name: loadControl
ChiValue.Notes: True when this EndDeviceAsset is capable of supporting load control functions through either the meter or the AMR option. To determine whether this functionality is installed and enabled, check the 'disabled' attribute of the associated device function contained by this EndDeviceAsset.

ChiValue.Name: reverseFlowHandling
ChiValue.Notes: True when this EndDeviceAsset is capable of supporting detection and monitoring of reverse flow.

ChiValue.Name: demandResponse
ChiValue.Notes: True when this EndDeviceAsset is capable of supporting demand response functions. To determine whether this functionality is installed and enabled, check the 'disabled' attribute of the associated device function contained by this EndDeviceAsset.

ChiValue.Name: metrology
ChiValue.Notes: True when this EndDeviceAsset is capable of supporting the presention of metered values to a user or another system (always true for a meter, but might not be true for a load control unit.)

ChiValue.Name: outageReport
ChiValue.Notes: True when this EndDeviceAsset is capable of supporting the means to report historical power interruption data.

ChiValue.Name: relayCapable
ChiValue.Notes: True if this EndDeviceAsset is capable of supporting one or more relays. The relays may be programmable in the meter and tied to TOU, time pulse, Load Control or other functions. To determine whether this functionality is installed and enabled, check the 'disabled' attribute of the associated device function contained by this EndDeviceAsset.

ChiValue.Name: readRequest
ChiValue.Notes: True when this EndDeviceAsset is capable of supporting on-request reads for this end device.

ChiValue.Name: dstEnabled
ChiValue.Notes: True when this EndDeviceAsset is capable of supporting the autonomous application of daylight savings time (DST).

ChiValue.Name: timeZoneOffset
ChiValue.Notes: Time zone offset relative to GMT for the location of the end device.

ChiValue.Name: amrSystem
ChiValue.Notes: Automated meter reading (AMR) system responsible for communications to the end device.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: EndDeviceControl
ChiNode.Notes: Instructs a meter to perform a specified action.

ChiValue.Name: scheduledInterval
ChiValue.Notes: (if control has scheduled duration) Date and time interval the control has been scheduled to execute within.

ChiValue.Name: priceSignal
ChiValue.Notes: Price is a parameter used for some MeterControls, such as real-time price signals.

ChiValue.Name: type
ChiValue.Notes: Type of control.

ChiValue.Name: drProgramLevel
ChiValue.Notes: Level of a demand response program request, where 0=emergency. Note: Attribute is not defined on DemandResponseProgram as it not its inherent property (it serves to conrol it).

ChiValue.Name: drProgramMandatory
ChiValue.Notes: Whether a demand response program request is mandatory. Note: Attribute is not defined on DemandResponseProgram as it not its inherent property (it serves to conrol it).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: EndDeviceEvent
ChiNode.Notes: Event detected by an EndDevice.

ChiValue.Name: userID
ChiValue.Notes: User ID for events that are user initiated.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: EndDeviceGroup
ChiNode.Notes: Abstraction for management of group communications within a two-way AMR system or the data for a group of related meters. Commands can be issued to all of the meters that belong to a meter group using a defined group address and the underlying AMR communication infrastructure.

ChiValue.Name: groupAddress
ChiValue.Notes: Address of meter group.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: IntervalBlock
ChiNode.Notes: Time sequence of Readings of the same ReadingType. Contained IntervalReadings may need conversion through the application of an offset and a scalar defined in associated Pending.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: IntervalReading
ChiNode.Notes:
Data captured at regular intervals of time. Interval data could be captured as incremental data, absolute data, or relative data. The source for the data is usually a tariff quantity or an engineering quantity. Data is typically captured in time-tagged, uniform, fixed-length intervals of 5, 10, 15, 30, or 60 minutes.
Note: Interval Data is sometimes also called "Interval Data Readings" (IDR).

ChiValue.Name: value
ChiValue.Notes: Value of the reading.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: MeterAsset
ChiNode.Notes: Physical asset that performs the metering role of the ServiceDeliveryPoint. Used for measuring consumption and detection of events.

ChiValue.Name: formNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Meter form designation per ANSI C12.10 or other applicable standard. An alphanumeric designation denoting the circuit arrangement for which the meter is applicable and its specific terminal arrangement.

ChiValue.Name: kR
ChiValue.Notes: Display multiplier used to produce a displayed value from a register value.

ChiValue.Name: kH
ChiValue.Notes: Meter kh (watthour) constant. It is the number of watthours that must be applied to the meter to cause one disk revolution for an electromechanical meter or the number of watthours represented by one increment pulse for an electronic meter.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: MeterReading
ChiNode.Notes: Quantity measured by a meter.

ChiValue.Name: valuesInterval
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time interval of the data items contained within meter reading.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: MeterServiceWork
ChiNode.Notes: Work involving meters.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Pending
ChiNode.Notes: When present, a scalar that is part of ReadingType and which needs to be applied to Reading.value in order to arrive at the true dimensions of a reading.

ChiValue.Name: scalarFloat
ChiValue.Notes: When the scalar needs to be presented as a floating value the ScalarFloat element will be populated. When multiplied with the Reading data value it causes a unit of measure conversion to occur, resulting in the Pending.UnitType unit of measure.

ChiValue.Name: scalarNumerator
ChiValue.Notes: When the scalar needs to be presented as an integer (or rational number) the ScalarNumerator element will be populated. When the scalar is a simple integer, and ScalarNumerator is presented alone and multiplied with the Reading data value, it causes a unit of measure conversion to occur ? resulting in the Pending.UnitType unit of measure. ScalarNumerator may be used in conjunction with ScalarDenominator, but not with ScalarFloat.

ChiValue.Name: scalarDenominator
ChiValue.Notes: When the scalar needs to be presented as a rational number, the ScalarDenominator element will be populated. When the Reading data value is multiplied by the ScalarNumerator, and divided by the ScalarDenominator, it causes a unit of measure conversion to occur ? resulting in the Pending.UnitType unit of measure.

ChiValue.Name: offset
ChiValue.Notes: Some systems require an offset to be added as well as multiplication using scalars.

ChiValue.Name: multiplyBeforeAdd
ChiValue.Notes: Whether scalars should be applied before adding the offset.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Reading
ChiNode.Notes: Specific value measured by a meter or other asset. Each Reading is associated with a specific ReadingType.

ChiValue.Name: value
ChiValue.Notes: Value of the reading.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ReadingQuality
ChiNode.Notes: Quality of a specific reading. Note that more than one Quality may be applicable to a given Reading. Typically not unsed unless problems or unusual conditions occur (i.e., quality for each Reading is assumed to be 'Good' unless stated otherwise in associated ReadingQuality).

ChiValue.Name: quality
ChiValue.Notes: Quality, to be specified if different than 'Good'.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ReadingType
ChiNode.Notes: Type of data conveyed by a specific Reading.

ChiValue.Name: kind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of reading.

ChiValue.Name: unit
ChiValue.Notes: Unit for the reading value.

ChiValue.Name: multiplier
ChiValue.Notes: Multiplier for the unit.

ChiValue.Name: intervalLength
ChiValue.Notes: Length of increment interval for incremental reading values (not applicable for absolute reading values).

ChiValue.Name: reverseChronology
ChiValue.Notes: True for systems that must operate in "reverse" chronological order.

ChiValue.Name: defaultValueDataType
ChiValue.Notes: The numeric type to be expected for the associated Block.value (e.g. defaultValueDataType= unsignedInteger).

ChiValue.Name: defaultQuality
ChiValue.Notes: Characteristics of a data value conveyed by a specific Reading, which allow an application to understand how a specific Reading is to be interpreted.

ChiValue.Name: dynamicConfiguration
ChiValue.Notes: Demand configuration such as block, rolling, logarithmic and sizes such as 15 minutes, 30 minutes, 5 minutes subinterval.

ChiValue.Name: channelNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Logical positioning of this measurement data.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Register
ChiNode.Notes: A quantity that is metered on an end device such as a meter.

ChiValue.Name: leftDigitCount
ChiValue.Notes: Number of digits (dials on a mechanical meter) to the left of the decimal place; default is 5.

ChiValue.Name: rightDigitCount
ChiValue.Notes: Number of digits (dials on a mechanical meter) to the right of the decimal place.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ServiceDeliveryPoint
ChiNode.Notes: Logical point on the network where the ownership of the service changes hands. It is one of potentially many service points within a ServiceLocation, delivering service in accordance with a CustomerAgreement. Used at the place where a meter may be installed.

ChiValue.Name: ctptReference
ChiValue.Notes: (optional for medium voltage connections) Reference to the low side terminal of a CT or PT, used to identify the specific CT or PT used to obtain a reading from a medium or high voltage point.

ChiValue.Name: grounded
ChiValue.Notes: True if grounded.

ChiValue.Name: nominalServiceVoltage
ChiValue.Notes: Nominal service voltage.

ChiValue.Name: phaseConfigurationKind
ChiValue.Notes: Phase configuration kind.

ChiValue.Name: servicePriority
ChiValue.Notes: Priority of service for this service point. Note that service points can have different priorities at the same service location.

ChiValue.Name: serviceDeliveryRemark
ChiValue.Notes: Remarks about this service delivery point, for example the reason for it being rated with a non-nominal priority.

ChiValue.Name: billingCycle
ChiValue.Notes: Billing cycle.

ChiValue.Name: loadMgmt
ChiValue.Notes: Load management code.

ChiValue.Name: estimatedLoad
ChiValue.Notes: Estimated load.

ChiValue.Name: budgetBill
ChiValue.Notes: Budget bill code.

ChiValue.Name: checkBilling
ChiValue.Notes: True if as a result of an inspection or otherwise, there is a reason to suspect that a previous billing may have been performed with erroneous data. Value should be reset once this potential discrepancy has been resolved.

ChiValue.Name: consumptionRealEnergy
ChiValue.Notes: Cumulative totalizing register of consumed service at this SDP over its lifetime.

ChiValue.Name: ratedCurrent
ChiValue.Notes: Current that this SDP is configured to deliver.

ChiValue.Name: ratedPower
ChiValue.Notes: Power that this SDP is configured to deliver.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AccountingUnit
ChiNode.Notes: Unit for accounting; use either 'energyUnit' or 'currencyUnit' to specify the unit for 'value'.

ChiValue.Name: energyUnit
ChiValue.Notes: Unit of service.

ChiValue.Name: value
ChiValue.Notes: Value expressed in applicable units.

ChiValue.Name: monetaryUnit
ChiValue.Notes: Unit of currency.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AccountMovement
ChiNode.Notes: Credit/debit movements for an account.

ChiValue.Name: amount
ChiValue.Notes: Amount that was credited to/debited from an account. For example: payment received/interest charge on arrears.

ChiValue.Name: reason
ChiValue.Notes: Reason for credit/debit transaction on an account. Example: payment received/arrears interest levied.

ChiValue.Name: dateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time when the credit/debit transaction was performed.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AuxiliaryAccount
ChiNode.Notes: The variable and dynamic part of AuxiliaryAgreement, generally representing the current state of the account related to the outstanding balance defined in AuxiliaryAgreement.

ChiValue.Name: balance
ChiValue.Notes: The total amount currently remaining on this AuxiliaryAccount that is required to be paid in order to settle the account to zero. This excludes any due amounts not yet paid.

ChiValue.Name: principleAmount
ChiValue.Notes: The initial principle amount, with which this AuxiliaryAccount was instantiated.

ChiValue.Name: due
ChiValue.Notes: Current amounts now due for payment on this AuxiliaryAccount.

ChiValue.Name: lastCredit
ChiValue.Notes: Details of the last credit transaction performed on this account.

ChiValue.Name: lastDebit
ChiValue.Notes: Details of the last debit transaction performed on this account.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AuxiliaryAgreement
ChiNode.Notes:
An ad-hoc auxiliary account agreement associated with a customer agreement, not part of the customer's account, but typically subject to formal agreement between customer and supplier (utility). Typically this is used to collect revenue owing by the customer for other services or arrears accrued with the utility for other services. It is typically linked to a prepaid token purchase transaction, thus forcing the customer to make a payment towards settlement of the auxiliary account balance whenever he needs to purchase a prepaid token for electricity.
The present status of AuxiliaryAgreement can be defined in the context of the utility's business rules, for example: enabled, disabled, pending, over recovered, under recovered, written off, etc.

ChiValue.Name: subCategory
ChiValue.Notes: Sub-category of this AuxiliaryAgreement as sub-classification of the inherited 'category'.

ChiValue.Name: auxCycle
ChiValue.Notes: The frequency for automatically recurring auxiliary charges, where AuxiliaryAccount.initialCharge is recursively added to AuxiliaryAccount.dueCurrent at the start of each auxCycle. For example: on a specified date and time; hourly; daily; weekly; monthly; 3-monthly; 6-monthly; 12-monthly; etc.

ChiValue.Name: auxPriorityCode
ChiValue.Notes: The coded priority indicating the priority that this AuxiliaryAgreement has above other AuxiliaryAgreements (associated with the same customer agreement) when it comes to competing for settlement from a payment transaction or token purchase.

ChiValue.Name: arrearsInterest
ChiValue.Notes: The interest per annum to be charged prorata on AuxiliaryAccount.dueArrears at the end of each payCycle.

ChiValue.Name: auxRef
ChiValue.Notes: A local reference to this AuxiliaryAgreement defined in the context of the implementation and not related to IdentifiedObject.mRID.

ChiValue.Name: payCycle
ChiValue.Notes: The contractually expected payment frequency (by the customer). Examples are: ad-hoc; on specified date; hourly, daily, weekly, monthly. etc.

ChiValue.Name: minAmount
ChiValue.Notes: The minimum amount that must be paid at any transaction towards settling this AuxiliryAgreement or reducing the balance.

ChiValue.Name: vendPortion
ChiValue.Notes: The percentage of the transaction amount that must be collected from each vending transaction towards settlement of this AuxiliaryAgreement when payments are not in arrears. Note that there may be multiple tokens vended per vending transaction, but this is not relevant.

ChiValue.Name: vendPortionArrear
ChiValue.Notes: The percentage of the transaction amount that must be collected from each vending transaction towards settlement of this AuxiliaryAgreement when payments are in arrears. Note that there may be multiple tokens vended per vending transaction, but this is not relevant.

ChiValue.Name: fixedAmount
ChiValue.Notes: The fixed amount that must be collected from each vending transaction towards settlement of this AuxiliaryAgreement. Note that there may be multiple tokens vended per vending transaction, but this is not relevant.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: BankAccountDetail
ChiNode.Notes: Details of a bank account.

ChiValue.Name: holderName
ChiValue.Notes: Name of account holder.

ChiValue.Name: holderID
ChiValue.Notes: National identity number (or equivalent) of account holder.

ChiValue.Name: accountNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Operational account reference number.

ChiValue.Name: bankName
ChiValue.Notes: Name of bank where account is held.

ChiValue.Name: branchCode
ChiValue.Notes: Branch of bank where account is held.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Card
ChiNode.Notes: Documentation of the tender when it is a type of card (credit, debit, etc).

ChiValue.Name: cvNumber
ChiValue.Notes: The card verification number.

ChiValue.Name: expiryDate
ChiValue.Notes: The date when this card expires.

ChiValue.Name: pan
ChiValue.Notes: The primary account number.

ChiValue.Name: accountHolderName
ChiValue.Notes: Name of account holder.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Cashier
ChiNode.Notes: The operator of the point of sale for the duration of CashierShift. Cashier is under the exclusive management control of Vendor.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CashierShift
ChiNode.Notes: The operating shift for a cashier, during which he may transact against the CashierShift, subject to VendorShift being open.

ChiValue.Name: cashFloat
ChiValue.Notes: The amount of cash that the cashier brings with him to start his shift and that he will take away at the end of his shift; i.e. the cash float does not get banked.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Charge
ChiNode.Notes: A charge element associated with other entities such as tariff structures, auxiliary agreements or other charge elements. The total charge amount applicable to this instance of Charge is the sum of fixedPortion plus percentagePortion.

ChiValue.Name: fixedPortion
ChiValue.Notes: The fixed portion of this charge element.

ChiValue.Name: kind
ChiValue.Notes: The kind of charge to be applied.

ChiValue.Name: variablePortion
ChiValue.Notes: The variable portion of this charge element, calculated as a percentage of the total amount of a parent charge.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Cheque
ChiNode.Notes: The actual tender when it is a type of cheque. Cheque reference number (as printed on the cheque) is specified in 'name.'

ChiValue.Name: date
ChiValue.Notes: Date when cheque becomes valid.

ChiValue.Name: kind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of cheque.

ChiValue.Name: micrNumber
ChiValue.Notes: The magnetic ink character recognition number printed on the cheque.

ChiValue.Name: chequeNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Cheque reference number as printed on the cheque.

ChiValue.Name: bankAccountDetail
ChiValue.Notes: Details of the account holder and bank.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ConsumptionTariffInterval
ChiNode.Notes: One of a sequence of intervals defined in terms of consumption quantity of a service such as electricity, water, gas, etc. It is typically used in association with TariffProfile to define the steps or blocks in a step tariff structure, where startValue simultaneously defines the entry value of this step and the closing value of the previous step. Where consumption is = startValue it falls within this interval and where consumption is startValue it falls within the previous interval.

ChiValue.Name: sequenceNumber
ChiValue.Notes: A sequential reference that defines the identity of this interval and its relative position with respect to other intervals in a sequence of intervals.

ChiValue.Name: startValue
ChiValue.Notes: The lowest level of consumption that defines the starting point of this interval. The interval extends to the start of the next interval or until it is reset to the start of the first interval by TariffProfile.tariffCycle.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Due
ChiNode.Notes: Details on amounts due for an account.

ChiValue.Name: current
ChiValue.Notes: Current total amount now due: current = principle + arrears + interest + charges. Typically the rule for settlement priority is: interest dues, then arrears dues, then current dues, then charge dues.

ChiValue.Name: principle
ChiValue.Notes: Part of current that constitutes the portion of the principle amount currently due.

ChiValue.Name: arrears
ChiValue.Notes: Part of current that constitutes the arrears portion.

ChiValue.Name: interest
ChiValue.Notes: Part of current that constitutes the interest portion.

ChiValue.Name: charges
ChiValue.Notes: Part of current that constitutes the charge portion: charges = Charge.fixedPortion + Charge.variablePortion.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: LineDetail
ChiNode.Notes: Details on an amount line, with rounding, date and note.

ChiValue.Name: amount
ChiValue.Notes: Amount for this line item.

ChiValue.Name: rounding
ChiValue.Notes: Totalised monetary value of all errors due to process rounding or truncating that is not reflected in 'amount'.

ChiValue.Name: dateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time when this line was created in the application process.

ChiValue.Name: note
ChiValue.Notes: Free format note relevant to this line.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: MerchantAccount
ChiNode.Notes: The operating account controlled by MerchantAgreement, against which Vendor may vend tokens or receipt payments. Transactions via VendorShift debit the account and bank deposits via BankStatement credit the account.

ChiValue.Name: currentBalance
ChiValue.Notes: The current operating balance of this account.

ChiValue.Name: provisionalBalance
ChiValue.Notes: The balance of this account after taking into account any pending debits from VendorShift.merchantDebitAmount and pending credits from BankStatement.merchantCreditAmount or credits (see also BankStatement attributes and VendorShift attributes).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: MerchantAgreement
ChiNode.Notes: A formal controlling contractual agreement between Supplier and Merchant, in terms of which Merchant is authorised to vend tokens and receipt payments on behalf of Supplier. Merchant is accountable to Supplier for revenue collected at PointOfSale.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: PaymentTransaction
ChiNode.Notes: Payment transaction.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: PointOfSale
ChiNode.Notes: Logical point where transactions take place with operational interaction between Cashier and the payment system; in certain cases PointOfSale interacts directly with the end customer, in which case Cashier might not be a real person: for example a self-service kiosk or over the internet.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Receipt
ChiNode.Notes: Record of total receipted payment from customer.

ChiValue.Name: isBankable
ChiValue.Notes: True if this receipted payment is manually bankable, otherwise it is an electronic funds transfer.

ChiValue.Name: line
ChiValue.Notes: Receipted amount with rounding, date and note.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ReceiptSummary
ChiNode.Notes: Record of detail of receipts pertaining to one shift of operation (one record per 'tenderKind').

ChiValue.Name: line
ChiValue.Notes: Totalised amount receipted during the shift for 'tenderKind', i.e., sum of ('Tender.amount' - 'Tender.change') per 'Tender.kind'.

ChiValue.Name: tenderKind
ChiValue.Notes: 'Tender.kind' for which 'receiptsTotal' is given.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ServiceSupplier
ChiNode.Notes: Organisation that provides services to Customers.

ChiValue.Name: issuerIdentificationNumber
ChiValue.Notes: Unique transaction reference prefix number issued to an entity by the International Standards Organisation for the purpose of tagging onto electronic financial transactions, as defined in ISO/IEC 7812-1 and ISO/IEC 7812-2.

ChiValue.Name: kind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of supplier.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Shift
ChiNode.Notes:
Generally referring to a period of operation or work performed. Whether shift is open/closed can be derived from attributes 'activiryInterval.start' and 'activityInterval.end'.
The grand total for receipts (i.e., cumulative total of all actual receipted amounts during this shift; bankable + non-bankable; excludes rounding error totals) can be derived from Receipt attributes:
=sum(Receipt.receiptAmount) ; includes bankable and non-bankable receipts.
Must also reconcile against:
=sum(receiptsGrandTotalBankable + receiptsGrandTotalNonBankable).
must also reconcile against ReceiptSummary:
=sum(ReceiptSummary.receiptsTotal).
The attributes with "GrandTotal" defined in this class may need to be used when the source data is periodically flushed from the system and then these cannot be derived.

ChiValue.Name: receiptsGrandTotalBankable
ChiValue.Notes:
Total of amounts receipted during this shift that can be manually banked (cash and cheques for example). Values are obtained from Receipt attributes:
=sum(Receipt.receiptAmount) for all Receipt.bankable = true.

ChiValue.Name: receiptsGrandTotalNonBankable
ChiValue.Notes:
Total of amounts receipted during this shift that cannot be manually banked (card payments for example). Values are obtained from Receipt attributes:
=sum(Receipt.receiptAmount) for all Receipt.bankable = false.

ChiValue.Name: receiptsGrandTotalRounding
ChiValue.Notes:
Cumulative amount in error due to process rounding not reflected in receiptsGrandTotal. Values are obtained from Receipt attributes:
=sum(Receipt.receiptRounding).

ChiValue.Name: activityInterval
ChiValue.Notes: Interval for activity of this shift.

ChiValue.Name: transactionsGrandTotal
ChiValue.Notes:
Cumulative total of transacted amounts during this shift. Values are obtained from Transaction attributes:
=sum(Transaction.transactionAmount). It must also reconcile against TransactionSummary:
=sum(TransactionSummary.transactionsTotal).

ChiValue.Name: transactionsGrandTotalRounding
ChiValue.Notes:
Cumulative amount in error due to process rounding not reflected in transactionsGandTotal. Values are obtained from Transaction attributes:
=sum(Transaction.transactionRounding).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TariffProfile
ChiNode.Notes: A schedule of charges; structure associated with Tariff that allows the definition of complex tarif structures such as step and time of use when used in conjunction with TariffInterval.intervalType and Charge. Inherited 'Status.status' is defined in the context of the utility's business rules; for example: active, inactive, etc.

ChiValue.Name: tariffCycle
ChiValue.Notes: The frequency at which the tariff charge schedule is repeated Examples are: once off on a specified date and time; hourly; daily; weekly; monthly; 3-monthly; 6-monthly; 12-monthly; etc. At the end of each cycle, the business rules are reset to start from the beginning again.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Tender
ChiNode.Notes:
Tender is what is "offered" by the customer towards making a payment and is often more than the required payment (hence the need for 'change'). The payment is thus that part of the Tender that goes towards settlement of a particular transaction.
Tender is modelled as an aggregation of Cheque and Card. Both these tender types can exist in a single tender bid thus 'accountHolderName' must exist separately in each of Cheque and Card as each could have a different account holder name.

ChiValue.Name: amount
ChiValue.Notes: Amount tendered by customer.

ChiValue.Name: change
ChiValue.Notes: Difference between amount tendered by customer and the amount charged by point of sale.

ChiValue.Name: kind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of tender from customer.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TimeTariffInterval
ChiNode.Notes: One of a sequence of time intervals defined in terms of real time. It is typically used in association with TariffProfile to define the intervals in a time of use tariff structure, where startDateTime simultaneously determines the starting point of this interval and the ending point of the previous interval.

ChiValue.Name: sequenceNumber
ChiValue.Notes: A sequential reference that defines the identity of this interval and its relative position with respect to other intervals in a sequence of intervals.

ChiValue.Name: startDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: A reatime marker that defines the starting time (typically it is the time of day) for this interval. The interval extends to the start of the next interval or until it is reset to the start of the first interval by TariffProfile.tariffCycle.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Transaction
ChiNode.Notes: The record of details of payment for service or token sale.

ChiValue.Name: receiverReference
ChiValue.Notes: Reference to the entity that is the recipient of 'amount' (for example, supplier for service charge payment; or tax receiver for VAT).

ChiValue.Name: donorReference
ChiValue.Notes: Reference to the entity that is the source of 'amount' (for example: customer for token purchase; or supplier for free issue token).

ChiValue.Name: diverseReference
ChiValue.Notes: Formal reference for use with diverse payment (traffic fine for example).

ChiValue.Name: reversedId
ChiValue.Notes: (if 'kind' is transactionReversal) Reference to the original transaction that is being reversed by this transaction.

ChiValue.Name: serviceUnitsEnergy
ChiValue.Notes: Actual amount of service units that is being paid for.

ChiValue.Name: serviceUnitsError
ChiValue.Notes: Number of service units not reflected in 'serviceUnitsEnergy' due to process rounding or truncating errors.

ChiValue.Name: kind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of transaction.

ChiValue.Name: line
ChiValue.Notes: Transaction amount, rounding, date and note for this transaction line.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TransactionSummary
ChiNode.Notes: The record of detail of payment transactions pertaining to one shift of operation (one record per 'transactionKind').

ChiValue.Name: line
ChiValue.Notes:
Totalised amount transacted during the shift for this specific 'transactionKind', i.e., sum of 'Transaction.line.amount' per 'Transaction.kind'.
Cumulative amount of rounding errors due to process rounding not reflected in 'LineDetail.amount' for 'transactionKind', i.e., sum of 'Transaction.line.rounding' per 'Transaction.kind'.

ChiValue.Name: transactionKind
ChiValue.Notes: 'Transaction.kind' for which 'transactionsTotal' is given.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Transactor
ChiNode.Notes: The entity that ultimately executes the transaction and who is in control of the process; typically this is embodied in secure software running on a server that may employ secure hardware encryption devices for secure transaction processing.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: VendingTransaction
ChiNode.Notes: Vending transaction.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Vendor
ChiNode.Notes: The entity that owns PointOfSale and contracts with Cashier to receipt payments and vend tokens using the payment system. Vendor has a private contract with and is managed by Merchant who is a type of Organisation. Vendor is accountable to Merchant for revenue collected, who is in turn accountable to Supplier.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: VendorShift
ChiNode.Notes: The operating shift for a vendor during which he may transact against the merchant's account. It aggregates transactions and receipts during the shift and periodically debits a merchant account. The totals in VendorShift should always = sum of totals aggregated in all cashier shifts that were open under the particular vendor shift.

ChiValue.Name: merchantDebitAmount
ChiValue.Notes: The amount that is to be debited from the merchant account for this vendor shift. This amount reflects the sum(PaymentTransaction.transactionAmount).

ChiValue.Name: posted
ChiValue.Notes: = true if merchantDebitAmount has been debited from MerchantAccount; typically happens at the end of VendorShift when it closes.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Work
ChiNode.Notes:
Document used to request, initiate, track and record work. This is synonymous with Work Breakdown Structure (WBS), which is traversed through the recursive association of Work.
Note that the work name is equal to the WBS name, which is given in the inherited "name" attribute. At the sub-work level (through recursion), the inherited "type" attribute indicates whether the work is capital, operations and maintenance, or other.

ChiValue.Name: kind
ChiValue.Notes: Kind of work.

ChiValue.Name: priority
ChiValue.Notes: Priority of work.

ChiValue.Name: requestDateTime
ChiValue.Notes: Date and time work was requested.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: IEC61970CIMVersion
ChiNode.Notes: This is the IEC 61970 CIM version number assigned to this UML model file.

ChiValue.Name: date
ChiValue.Notes: Form is YYYY-MM-DD for example for January 5, 2009 it is 2009-01-05.

ChiValue.Name: version
ChiValue.Notes: Form is IEC61970CIMXXvYY where XX is the major CIM package version and the YY is the minor version. For ecample IEC61970CIM13v18.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Contingency
ChiNode.Notes: An event threatening system reliability, consisting of one or more contingency elements.

ChiValue.Name: mustStudy
ChiValue.Notes: Set true if must study this contingency.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ContingencyElement
ChiNode.Notes: An element of a system event to be studied by contingency analysis, representing a change in status of a single piece of equipment.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ContingencyEquipment
ChiNode.Notes: A equipment to which the in service status is to change such as a power transformer or AC line segment.

ChiValue.Name: contingentStatus
ChiValue.Notes: The status for the associated equipment when in the contingency state. This status is independent of the case to which the contingency is originally applied, but defines the equipment status when the contingency is applied.

Package.Name: ControlArea
Package.Notes: The ControlArea package models area specifications which can be used for a variety of purposes. The package as a whole models potentially overlapping control area specifications for the purpose of actual generation control, load forecast area load capture, or powerflow based analysis.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AltGeneratingUnitMeas
ChiNode.Notes: A prioritized measurement to be used for the generating unit in the control area specificaiton.

ChiValue.Name: priority
ChiValue.Notes: Priority of a measurement usage. Lower numbers have first priority.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AltTieMeas
ChiNode.Notes: A prioritized measurement to be used for the tie flow as part of the control area specification.

ChiValue.Name: priority
ChiValue.Notes: Priority of a measurement usage. Lower numbers have first priority.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ControlArea
ChiNode.Notes: A control area is a grouping of generating units and/or loads and a cutset of tie lines (as terminals) which may be used for a variety of purposes including automatic generation control, powerflow solution area interchange control specification, and input to load forecasting. Note that any number of overlapping control area specifications can be superimposed on the physical model.

ChiValue.Name: netInterchange
ChiValue.Notes: The specified positive net interchange into the control area.

ChiValue.Name: pTolerance
ChiValue.Notes: Active power net interchange tolerance

ChiValue.Name: type

ChiNode.Name: IdentifiedObject
ChiNode.Notes:
This is a root class to provide common naming attributes for all classes needing naming attributes.

In the EEnergy default model this class is Abstract, so don't has any actual implementation.

ChiValue.Name: mRID
ChiValue.Notes: A Model Authority issues mRIDs. Given that each Model Authority has a unique id and this id is part of the mRID, then the mRID is globally unique.

ChiValue.Name: name
ChiValue.Notes: The name is a free text human readable name of the object. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy.

ChiValue.Name: localName
ChiValue.Notes: The localName is a human readable name of the object. It is only used with objects organized in a naming hierarchy. The simplest naming hierarchy has just one parent (the root) giving a flat naming hierarchy. However, the naming hierarchy usually has several levels, e.g. Substation, VoltageLevel, Equipment etc. Children of the same parent have names that are unique among them. If the uniqueness requirement cannot be met IdentifiedObject.localName shall not be used, use IdentifiedObject.name instead.

ChiValue.Name: pathName
ChiValue.Notes: The pathname is a system unique name composed from all IdentifiedObject.localNames in a naming hierarchy path from the object to the root.

ChiValue.Name: aliasName
ChiValue.Notes: The aliasName is free text human readable name of the object alternative to IdentifiedObject.name. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy.

ChiValue.Name: description
ChiValue.Notes: The description is a free human readable text describing or naming the object. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy.

Package.Name: Domain
Package.Notes:
The domain package is a data dictionary of quantities and units that define datatypes for attributes (properties) that may be used by any class in any other package.
This package contains the definition of primitive datatypes, including units of measure and permissible values. Each datatype contains a value attribute and an optional unit of measure, which is specified as a static variable initialized to the textual description of the unit of measure. The value of the "units" string may be country or customer specific. Typical values are given. Permissible values for enumerations are listed in the documentation for the attribute using UML constraint syntax inside curly braces. Lengths of variable strings are listed in the descriptive text where required.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Subcritical
ChiNode.Notes: Once-through subcritical boiler

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Supercritical
ChiNode.Notes: Once-through supercritical boiler

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: AirCompressor
ChiNode.Notes: Combustion turbine air compressor which is an integral part of a compressed air energy storage (CAES) plant

ChiValue.Name: airCompressorRating
ChiValue.Notes: Rating of the CAES air compressor

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CAESPlant
ChiNode.Notes: Compressed air energy storage plant

ChiValue.Name: energyStorageCapacity
ChiValue.Notes: The rated energy storage capacity.

ChiValue.Name: ratedCapacityP
ChiValue.Notes: The CAES plant's gross rated generating capacity

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Classification
ChiNode.Notes: 1..n, with 1 the most detailed, highest priority, etc.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CogenerationPlant
ChiNode.Notes: A set of thermal generating units for the production of electrical energy and process steam (usually from the output of the steam turbines). The steam sendout is typically used for industrial purposes or for municipal heating and cooling.

ChiValue.Name: cogenHPSendoutRating
ChiValue.Notes: The high pressure steam sendout

ChiValue.Name: cogenHPSteamRating
ChiValue.Notes: The high pressure steam rating

ChiValue.Name: cogenLPSendoutRating
ChiValue.Notes: The low pressure steam sendout

ChiValue.Name: cogenLPSteamRating
ChiValue.Notes: The low pressure steam rating

ChiValue.Name: ratedP
ChiValue.Notes: The rated output active power of the cogeneration plant

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CombinedCyclePlant
ChiNode.Notes: A set of combustion turbines and steam turbines where the exhaust heat from the combustion turbines is recovered to make steam for the steam turbines, resulting in greater overall plant efficiency

ChiValue.Name: combCyclePlantRating
ChiValue.Notes: The combined cycle plant's active power output rating

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CostPerHeatUnit
ChiNode.Notes: Cost, in units of currency, per quantity of heat generated

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Emission
ChiNode.Notes: Quantity of emission per fuel heat content

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: EmissionAccount
ChiNode.Notes: Accounts for tracking emissions usage and credits for thermal generating units. A unit may have zero or more emission accounts, and will typically have one for tracking usage and one for tracking credits.

ChiValue.Name: emissionType
ChiValue.Notes: The type of emission, for example sulfur dioxide (SO2). The y1AxisUnits of the curve contains the unit of measure (e.g. kg) and the emissionType is the type of emission (e.g. sulfer dioxide).

ChiValue.Name: emissionValueSource
ChiValue.Notes: The source of the emission value.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: EmissionCurve
ChiNode.Notes: Relationship between the unit's emission rate in units of mass per hour (Y-axis) and output active power (X-axis) for a given type of emission. This curve applies when only one type of fuel is being burned.

ChiValue.Name: emissionContent
ChiValue.Notes: The emission content per quantity of fuel burned

ChiValue.Name: emissionType
ChiValue.Notes: The type of emission, which also gives the production rate measurement unit. The y1AxisUnits of the curve contains the unit of measure (e.g. kg) and the emissionType is the type of emission (e.g. sulfer dioxide).

ChiValue.Name: isNetGrossP
ChiValue.Notes: Flag is set to true when output is expressed in net active power

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: FossilFuel
ChiNode.Notes: The fossil fuel consumed by the non-nuclear thermal generating units, e.g., coal, oil, gas

ChiValue.Name: fossilFuelType
ChiValue.Notes: The type of fossil fuel, such as coal, oil, or gas.

ChiValue.Name: fuelCost
ChiValue.Notes: The cost in terms of heat value for the given type of fuel

ChiValue.Name: fuelDispatchCost
ChiValue.Notes: The cost of fuel used for economic dispatching which includes: fuel cost, transportation cost, and incremental maintenance cost

ChiValue.Name: fuelEffFactor
ChiValue.Notes: The efficiency factor for the fuel (per unit) in terms of the effective energy absorbed

ChiValue.Name: fuelHandlingCost
ChiValue.Notes: Handling and processing cost associated with this fuel

ChiValue.Name: fuelHeatContent
ChiValue.Notes: The amount of heat per weight (or volume) of the given type of fuel

ChiValue.Name: fuelMixture
ChiValue.Notes: Relative amount of the given type of fuel, when multiple fuels are being consumed.

ChiValue.Name: fuelSulfur
ChiValue.Notes: The fuel's fraction of pollution credit per unit of heat content

ChiValue.Name: highBreakpointP
ChiValue.Notes: The active power output level of the unit at which the given type of fuel is switched on. This fuel (e.g., oil) is sometimes used to supplement the base fuel (e.g., coal) at high active power output levels.

ChiValue.Name: lowBreakpointP
ChiValue.Notes: The active power output level of the unit at which the given type of fuel is switched off. This fuel (e.g., oil) is sometimes used to stabilize the base fuel (e.g., coal) at low active power output levels.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: FuelAllocationSchedule
ChiNode.Notes: The amount of fuel of a given type which is allocated for consumption over a specified period of time

ChiValue.Name: fuelAllocationEndDate
ChiValue.Notes: The end time and date of the fuel allocation schedule

ChiValue.Name: fuelAllocationStartDate
ChiValue.Notes: The start time and date of the fuel allocation schedule

ChiValue.Name: fuelType
ChiValue.Notes: The type of fuel, which also indicates the corresponding measurement unit

ChiValue.Name: maxFuelAllocation
ChiValue.Notes: The maximum amount fuel that is allocated for consumption for the scheduled time period

ChiValue.Name: minFuelAllocation
ChiValue.Notes: The minimum amount fuel that is allocated for consumption for the scheduled time period, e.g., based on a "take-or-pay" contract

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GeneratingUnit
ChiNode.Notes: A single or set of synchronous machines for converting mechanical power into alternating-current power. For example, individual machines within a set may be defined for scheduling purposes while a single control signal is derived for the set. In this case there would be a GeneratingUnit for each member of the set and an additional GeneratingUnit corresponding to the set.

ChiValue.Name: allocSpinResP
ChiValue.Notes: The planned unused capacity (spinning reserve) which can be used to support emergency load

ChiValue.Name: autoCntrlMarginP
ChiValue.Notes: The planned unused capacity which can be used to support automatic control overruns.

ChiValue.Name: baseP
ChiValue.Notes: For dispatchable units, this value represents the economic active power basepoint, for units that are not dispatchable, this value represents the fixed generation value. The value must be between the operating low and high limits.

ChiValue.Name: controlDeadband
ChiValue.Notes: Unit control error deadband. When a unit's desired active power change is less than this deadband, then no control pulses will be sent to the unit.

ChiValue.Name: controlPulseHigh
ChiValue.Notes: Pulse high limit which is the largest control pulse that the unit can respond to

ChiValue.Name: controlPulseLow
ChiValue.Notes: Pulse low limit which is the smallest control pulse that the unit can respond to

ChiValue.Name: controlResponseRate
ChiValue.Notes: Unit response rate which specifies the active power change for a control pulse of one second in the most responsive loading level of the unit.

ChiValue.Name: efficiency
ChiValue.Notes: The efficiency of the unit in converting mechanical energy, from the prime mover, into electrical energy.

ChiValue.Name: genControlMode
ChiValue.Notes: The unit control mode.

ChiValue.Name: genControlSource
ChiValue.Notes: The source of controls for a generating unit.

ChiValue.Name: genOperatingMode
ChiValue.Notes: Operating mode for secondary control.

ChiValue.Name: governorMPL
ChiValue.Notes: Governor Motor Position Limit

ChiValue.Name: governorSCD
ChiValue.Notes: Governor Speed Changer Droop

ChiValue.Name: highControlLimit
ChiValue.Notes: High limit for secondary (AGC) control

ChiValue.Name: initialP
ChiValue.Notes: Default Initial active power which is used to store a powerflow result for the initial active power for this unit in this network configuration

ChiValue.Name: longPF
ChiValue.Notes: Generating unit economic participation factor

ChiValue.Name: lowControlLimit
ChiValue.Notes: Low limit for secondary (AGC) control

ChiValue.Name: maxEconomicP
ChiValue.Notes: Maximum high economic active power limit, that should not exceed the maximum operating active power limit

ChiValue.Name: maximumAllowableSpinningReserve
ChiValue.Notes: Maximum allowable spinning reserve. Spinning reserve will never be considered greater than this value regardless of the current operating point.

ChiValue.Name: maxOperatingP
ChiValue.Notes: This is the maximum operating active power limit the dispatcher can enter for this unit

ChiValue.Name: minEconomicP
ChiValue.Notes: Low economic active power limit that must be greater than or equal to the minimum operating active power limit

ChiValue.Name: minimumOffTime
ChiValue.Notes: Minimum time interval between unit shutdown and startup

ChiValue.Name: minOperatingP
ChiValue.Notes: This is the minimum operating active power limit the dispatcher can enter for this unit.

ChiValue.Name: modelDetail
ChiValue.Notes: Detail level of the generator model data

ChiValue.Name: normalPF
ChiValue.Notes: Generating unit economic participation factor

ChiValue.Name: penaltyFactor
ChiValue.Notes: Defined as: 1 / ( 1 - Incremental Transmission Loss); with the Incremental Transmission Loss expressed as a plus or minus value. The typical range of penalty factors is (0.9 to 1.1).

ChiValue.Name: ratedGrossMaxP
ChiValue.Notes: The unit's gross rated maximum capacity (Book Value).

ChiValue.Name: ratedGrossMinP
ChiValue.Notes: The gross rated minimum generation level which the unit can safely operate at while delivering power to the transmission grid

ChiValue.Name: ratedNetMaxP
ChiValue.Notes: The net rated maximum capacity determined by subtracting the auxiliary power used to operate the internal plant machinery from the rated gross maximum capacity

ChiValue.Name: shortPF
ChiValue.Notes: Generating unit economic participation factor

ChiValue.Name: startupCost
ChiValue.Notes: The initial startup cost incurred for each start of the GeneratingUnit.

ChiValue.Name: startupTime
ChiValue.Notes: Time it takes to get the unit on-line, from the time that the prime mover mechanical power is applied

ChiValue.Name: tieLinePF
ChiValue.Notes: Generating unit economic participation factor

ChiValue.Name: variableCost
ChiValue.Notes: The variable cost component of production per unit of ActivePower.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GenUnitOpCostCurve
ChiNode.Notes: Relationship between unit operating cost (Y-axis) and unit output active power (X-axis). The operating cost curve for thermal units is derived from heat input and fuel costs. The operating cost curve for hydro units is derived from water flow rates and equivalent water costs.

ChiValue.Name: isNetGrossP
ChiValue.Notes: Flag is set to true when output is expressed in net active power

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GenUnitOpSchedule
ChiNode.Notes: The generating unit's Operator-approved current operating schedule (or plan), typically produced with the aid of unit commitment type analyses. The X-axis represents absolute time. The Y1-axis represents the status (0=off-line and unavailable: 1=available: 2=must run: 3=must run at fixed power value: etc.). The Y2-axis represents the must run fixed power value where required.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: GrossToNetActivePowerCurve
ChiNode.Notes: Relationship between the generating unit's gross active power output on the X-axis (measured at the terminals of the machine(s)) and the generating unit's net active power output on the Y-axis (based on utility-defined measurements at the power station). Station service loads, when modeled, should be treated as non-conforming bus loads. There may be more than one curve, depending on the auxiliary equipment that is in service.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: HeatInputCurve
ChiNode.Notes: Relationship between unit heat input in energy per time for main fuel (Y1-axis) and supplemental fuel (Y2-axis) versus unit output in active power (X-axis). The quantity of main fuel used to sustain generation at this output level is prorated for throttling between definition points. The quantity of supplemental fuel used at this output level is fixed and not prorated.

ChiValue.Name: auxPowerMult
ChiValue.Notes: Power output - auxiliary power multiplier adjustment factor.

ChiValue.Name: auxPowerOffset
ChiValue.Notes: Power output - auxiliary power offset adjustment factor

ChiValue.Name: heatInputEff
ChiValue.Notes: Heat input - efficiency multiplier adjustment factor.

ChiValue.Name: heatInputOffset
ChiValue.Notes: Heat input - offset adjustment factor.

ChiValue.Name: isNetGrossP
ChiValue.Notes: Flag is set to true when output is expressed in net active power

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: HeatRate
ChiNode.Notes: Heat generated, in energy pertime unit of elapsed time

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: HeatRateCurve
ChiNode.Notes: Relationship between unit heat rate per active power (Y-axis) and unit output (X-axis). The heat input is from all fuels.

ChiValue.Name: isNetGrossP
ChiValue.Notes: Flag is set to true when output is expressed in net active power

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: HydroGeneratingEfficiencyCurve
ChiNode.Notes:
Relationship between unit efficiency in percent and unit output active power for a given net head in meters. The relationship between efficiency, discharge, head, and power output is expressed as follows: E =KP/HQ
Where: (E=percentage) (P=active power) (H=height) (Q=volume/time unit) (K=constant)
For example, a curve instance for a given net head could relate efficiency (Y-axis) versus active power output (X-axis) or versus discharge on the X-axis.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: HydroGeneratingUnit
ChiNode.Notes: A generating unit whose prime mover is a hydraulic turbine (e.g., Francis, Pelton, Kaplan)

ChiValue.Name: hydroUnitWaterCost
ChiValue.Notes: The equivalent cost of water that drives the hydro turbine, expressed as cost per volume.

ChiValue.Name: energyConversionCapability
ChiValue.Notes: Energy conversion capability for generating.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: HydroPowerPlant
ChiNode.Notes: A hydro power station which can generate or pump. When generating, the generator turbines receive there water from an upper reservoir. When pumping, the pumps receive their water from a lower reservoir.

ChiValue.Name: dischargeTravelDelay
ChiValue.Notes: Water travel delay from tailbay to next downstream hydro power station

ChiValue.Name: hydroPlantType
ChiValue.Notes: The type of hydro power plant.

ChiValue.Name: penstockType
ChiValue.Notes: Type and configuration of hydro plant penstock(s)

ChiValue.Name: plantDischargeCapacity
ChiValue.Notes: Total plant discharge capacity in cubic meters per second

ChiValue.Name: genRatedP
ChiValue.Notes: The hydro plant's generating rating active power for rated head conditions

ChiValue.Name: pumpRatedP
ChiValue.Notes: The hydro plant's pumping rating active power for rated head conditions

ChiValue.Name: plantRatedHead
ChiValue.Notes: The plant's rated gross head in meters

ChiValue.Name: surgeTankCode
ChiValue.Notes: A code describing the type (or absence) of surge tank that is associated with the hydro power plant

ChiValue.Name: surgeTankCrestLevel
ChiValue.Notes: The level at which the surge tank spills

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: HydroPump
ChiNode.Notes: A synchronous motor-driven pump, typically associated with a pumped storage plant

ChiValue.Name: pumpDischAtMaxHead
ChiValue.Notes: The pumping discharge (m3/sec) under maximum head conditions, usually at full gate

ChiValue.Name: pumpDischAtMinHead
ChiValue.Notes: The pumping discharge (m3/sec) under minimum head conditions, usually at full gate

ChiValue.Name: pumpPowerAtMaxHead
ChiValue.Notes: The pumping power under maximum head conditions, usually at full gate

ChiValue.Name: pumpPowerAtMinHead
ChiValue.Notes: The pumping power under minimum head conditions, usually at full gate.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: HydroPumpOpSchedule
ChiNode.Notes: The hydro pump's Operator-approved current operating schedule (or plan), typically produced with the aid of unit commitment type analyses.The unit's operating schedule status is typically given as: (0=unavailable) (1=avilable to startup or shutdown) (2=must pump)

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: IncrementalHeatRateCurve
ChiNode.Notes: Relationship between unit incremental heat rate in (delta energy/time) per (delta active power) and unit output in active power. The IHR curve represents the slope of the HeatInputCurve. Note that the "incremental heat rate" and the "heat rate" have the same engineering units.

ChiValue.Name: isNetGrossP
ChiValue.Notes: Flag is set to true when output is expressed in net active power

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: InflowForecast
ChiNode.Notes: Natural water inflow to a reservoir, usually forecasted from predicted rain and snowmelt. Typically in one hour increments for up to 10 days. The forecast is given in average cubic meters per second over the time increment.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: LevelVsVolumeCurve
ChiNode.Notes: Relationship between reservoir volume and reservoir level. The volume is at the y-axis and the reservoir level at the x-axis.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: NuclearGeneratingUnit
ChiNode.Notes: A nuclear generating unit.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: PenstockLossCurve
ChiNode.Notes: Relationship between penstock head loss (in meters) and total discharge through the penstock (in cubic meters per second). One or more turbines may be connected to the same penstock.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Reservoir
ChiNode.Notes: A water storage facility within a hydro system, including: ponds, lakes, lagoons, and rivers. The storage is usually behind some type of dam.

ChiValue.Name: activeStorageCapacity
ChiValue.Notes: Storage volume between the full supply level and the normal minimum operating level

ChiValue.Name: energyStorageRating
ChiValue.Notes: The reservoir's energy storage rating in energy for given head conditions

ChiValue.Name: fullSupplyLevel
ChiValue.Notes: Full supply level, above which water will spill. This can be the spillway crest level or the top of closed gates.

ChiValue.Name: grossCapacity
ChiValue.Notes: Total capacity of reservoir

ChiValue.Name: normalMinOperateLevel
ChiValue.Notes: Normal minimum operating level below which the penstocks will draw air

ChiValue.Name: riverOutletWorks
ChiValue.Notes: River outlet works for riparian right releases or other purposes

ChiValue.Name: spillTravelDelay
ChiValue.Notes: The spillway water travel delay to the next downstream reservoir

ChiValue.Name: spillwayCapacity
ChiValue.Notes: The flow capacity of the spillway in cubic meters per second

ChiValue.Name: spillwayCrestLength
ChiValue.Notes: The length of the spillway crest in meters

ChiValue.Name: spillwayCrestLevel
ChiValue.Notes: Spillway crest level above which water will spill

ChiValue.Name: spillWayGateType
ChiValue.Notes: Type of spillway gate, including parameters

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ShutdownCurve
ChiNode.Notes: Relationship between the rate in gross active power/minute (Y-axis) at which a unit should be shutdown and its present gross MW output (X-axis)

ChiValue.Name: shutdownCost
ChiValue.Notes: Fixed shutdown cost

ChiValue.Name: shutdownDate
ChiValue.Notes: The date and time of the most recent generating unit shutdown

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: SpillwayGateType
ChiNode.Notes: Type of spillway gate.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: StartIgnFuelCurve
ChiNode.Notes: The quantity of ignition fuel (Y-axis) used to restart and repay the auxiliary power consumed versus the number of hours (X-axis) the unit was off line

ChiValue.Name: ignitionFuelType
ChiValue.Notes: Type of ignition fuel

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: StartMainFuelCurve
ChiNode.Notes: The quantity of main fuel (Y-axis) used to restart and repay the auxiliary power consumed versus the number of hours (X-axis) the unit was off line

ChiValue.Name: mainFuelType
ChiValue.Notes: Type of main fuel

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: StartRampCurve
ChiNode.Notes: Rate in gross active power/minute (Y-axis) at which a unit can be loaded versus the number of hours (X-axis) the unit was off line

ChiValue.Name: hotStandbyRamp
ChiValue.Notes: The startup ramp rate in gross for a unit that is on hot standby

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: StartupModel
ChiNode.Notes: Unit start up characteristics depending on how long the unit has been off line

ChiValue.Name: fixedMaintCost
ChiValue.Notes: Fixed Maintenance Cost

ChiValue.Name: hotStandbyHeat
ChiValue.Notes: The amount of heat input per time uint required for hot standby operation

ChiValue.Name: incrementalMaintCost
ChiValue.Notes: Incremental Maintenance Cost

ChiValue.Name: minimumDownTime
ChiValue.Notes: The minimum number of hours the unit must be down before restart

ChiValue.Name: minimumRunTime
ChiValue.Notes: The minimum number of hours the unit must be operating before being allowed to shut down

ChiValue.Name: riskFactorCost
ChiValue.Notes: The opportunity cost associated with the return in monetary unit. This represents the restart's "share" of the unit depreciation and risk of an event which would damage the unit.

ChiValue.Name: startupCost
ChiValue.Notes: Total miscellaneous start up costs

ChiValue.Name: startupDate
ChiValue.Notes: The date and time of the most recent generating unit startup

ChiValue.Name: startupPriority
ChiValue.Notes: Startup priority within control area where lower numbers indicate higher priorities. More than one unit in an area may be assigned the same priority.

ChiValue.Name: stbyAuxP
ChiValue.Notes: The unit's auxiliary active power consumption to maintain standby mode

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: SteamSendoutSchedule
ChiNode.Notes: The cogeneration plant's steam sendout schedule in volume per time unit.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TailbayLossCurve
ChiNode.Notes: Relationship between tailbay head loss hight (y-axis) and the total discharge into the power station's tailbay volume per time unit (x-axis) . There could be more than one curve depending on the level of the tailbay reservoir or river level

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: TargetLevelSchedule
ChiNode.Notes: Reservoir water level targets from advanced studies or "rule curves". Typically in one hour increments for up to 10 days

ChiValue.Name: highLevelLimit
ChiValue.Notes: High target level limit, above which the reservoir operation will be penalized

ChiValue.Name: lowLevelLimit
ChiValue.Notes: Low target level limit, below which the reservoir operation will be penalized

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ThermalGeneratingUnit
ChiNode.Notes: A generating unit whose prime mover could be a steam turbine, combustion turbine, or diesel engine. Additional Thermal types shown on Thermal diagram

ChiValue.Name: oMCost
ChiValue.Notes: Operating and maintenance cost for the thermal unit

Package.Name: LoadModel
Package.Notes:
This package is responsible for modeling the energy consumers and the system load as curves and associated curve data. Special circumstances that may affect the load, such as seasons and daytypes, are also included here.
This information is used by Load Forecasting and Load Management.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ConformLoad
ChiNode.Notes: ConformLoad represent loads that follow a daily load change pattern where the pattern can be used to scale the load with a system load.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ConformLoadGroup
ChiNode.Notes: Load that follows a daily and seasonal load variation pattern.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: ConformLoadSchedule
ChiNode.Notes: A curve of load versus time (X-axis) showing the active power values (Y1-axis) and reactive power (Y2-axis) for each unit of the period covered. This curve represents a typical pattern of load over the time period for a given day type and season.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: CustomerLoad
ChiNode.Notes: A meter for measuring customer energy consumption. The typeName attribute indicates the type of customer meter.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: DayType
ChiNode.Notes: Group of similar days, e.g., Mon/Tue/Wed, Thu/Fri, Sat/Sun, Holiday1, Holiday2

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: EnergyArea
ChiNode.Notes: The class describes an area having energy production or consumption. The class is the basis for further specialization.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: InductionMotorLoad
ChiNode.Notes: Large three phase induction motor load. The typeName attribute indicates the type of induction motor (1 = wound rotor) (2 = squirrel cage).

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: Load
ChiNode.Notes: A generic equivalent for an energy consumer on a transmission or distribution voltage level. It may be under load management and also has cold load pick up characteristics.

ChiValue.Name: coldPickUpFactorQ
ChiValue.Notes: The amount of nominal feeder reactive power that is picked up cold.

ChiValue.Name: coldPickUpFactorP
ChiValue.Notes: The amount of nominal feeder active power that is picked up cold.

ChiValue.Name: feederLoadMgtFactor
ChiValue.Notes: The feeder's contribution to load management.

ChiValue.Name: phaseRatedCurrent
ChiValue.Notes: The rated individual phase current.

ChiValue.Name: loadAllocationFactor
ChiValue.Notes: Permit assignment of loads on a participation factor basis. Given three equivalent loads with factors of 10, 25 and 15, a feeder load of 100 amps could be allocated on the feeder as 20, 50 and 30 amps.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: LoadArea
ChiNode.Notes: The class is the root or first level in a hierarchical structure for grouping of loads for the purpose of load flow load scaling.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: LoadGroup
ChiNode.Notes: The class is the third level in a hierarchical structure for grouping of loads for the purpose of load flow load scaling.

ChiNode.creator: admin
ChiNode.Name: LoadResponseCharacteristic
ChiNode.Notes: Models the characteristic response of the load demand due to to changes in system conditions such as voltage and frequency. This is not related to demand response.

ChiValue.Name: exponentModel
ChiValue.Notes: Indicates the exponential voltage dependency model (pVoltateExponent and qVoltageExponent) is to be used. If false, the coeficient model (consisting of pConstantImpedance, pConstantCurrent, pConstantPower, qConstantImpedance, qConstantCurrent, and qConstantPower) is to be used.

ChiValue.Name: pConstantCurrent
ChiValue.Notes: Portion of active power load modeled as constant current. Used only if the useExponentModel is false. This value is noralized against the sum of pZ, pI, and pP.

ChiValue.Name: pConstantImpedance
ChiValue.Notes: Portion of active power load modeled as constant impedance. Used only if the useExponentModel is false. This value is noralized against the sum of pZ, pI, and pP.

ChiValue.Name: pConstantPower
